Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the second innings! The Aussies stride out to the middle and they are followed by Zak Crawley and Rory Burns who will open the batting for England. Mitchell Starc has the pink ball in his hand. Here we go...
... Second innings ...

After opting to bowl first, on a green top, England have fared reasonably well at the Bellerive Oval. It was Ollie Robinson who set the tone for the tourists on Day 1 as he sent back the dangerous David Warner and Steve Smith for a duck. Usman Khawaja, the man in red-hot form was also dismissed cheaply for just 6 runs and England were all over Australia at one point. However, the tourists failed to capitalize on the start and leaked some runs once Travis Head joined Labuschagne. Mark Wood bowled his heart out and he trapped a couple of Aussie batters with his pacy bouncers. Although, the English side suffered a huge blow as Ollie Robinson had to walk off the field due to stiff back and the Aussies took good advantage of that. Woakes also grabbed a couple of wickets but even he was a touch expensive. Wood came roaring back on Day 2 and he got rid of Cummins and Starc with some short-pitched stuff. All in all, it was a good bowling performance from England but they would have liked to wrap the innings up much earlier than they did. The English bowlers have done their job and it is now upto their batters to put on a good show in the first innings. Do join us for the second innings which will begin soon.

Well, what a first innings we have witnessed in this final Test of the series. It started with England picking up early wickets on Day 1 and then it was Marnus Labuschagne and Travis Head who steadied the ship for the hosts. Head made a grand comeback into this Test and notched up his fourth Test hundred. Cameron Green also played a very vital innings for the hosts and the pair of Head and Green stitched together a partnership of 121 runs. This partnership swung the momentum in Australia's favour. It was Nathan Lyon who swung his willow at the fag end of the innings and that propelled Australia to go past the 300-run mark.

OUT! Cleaned up! Stuart Broad knocks over Nathan Lyon and the Aussies are finally bundled out. Broad bowls a length ball, right on top of off and that's where you want to be as a pacer. Lyon backs away and looks to clobber it on the leg side but gets comprehensively beaten. The ball goes on to knock over the bails and Broad has his third wicket. Australia finish with 303 runs on the board.
Commentary.Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Just about keeps it out does Nathan Lyon. Fullish ball, tailing into middle and leg. Lyon does well to get a bat on it.
A length ball, around middle. Lyon hangs deep and flicks it through square leg, albeit a bit awkwardly and picks up another couple of runs.
Broad looks for the inswinging yorker, on off. Lyon digs it out.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on off. Lyon works it wide of mid on for one.

DROPPED! A great effort by Billings though! Back of a length, on off. Lyon goes for the slog but gets the top edge this time. The ball goes high in the air towards square leg. Billings gives it a chase and almost gets there too. He puts in a dive but it goes just past his fingertips. That brings up 300 for Australia.
FOUR! Oh, that is flayed away! Shorter and wider outside off. Lyon rocks back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary.
Short this time, outside off. Lyon misses the pull.
On a length, on off. Lyon pushes it towards cover.
Mark Wood (17-1-108-3) is back on.
Fuller and a bit wider outside off. Boland leaves it.
A dot ball as Boland is solid in his defence.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on the pads. Lyon works it past square leg for one.
Fuller, on the pads. Flicked to the leg side.
Length, around off. Lyon gets the outside edge but it drops short of gully.

Drinks! The ball has already been changed once and looks like this one has gone soft as well. As the umpires choose a replacement, the players take drinks. By the looks of it, it has been England's morning so far but not quite. They need just one more wicket to wrap proceedings but have conceded over 50 runs and the closer and closer Australia gets to 300, the visitors will find it that much more difficult.
Fuller and outside off. Boland gets the outside edge through the slip cordon for a couple this time.
FOUR! Oh, that is a top shot! Full, on the pads. Boland flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Well bowled and well played. Woakes slips a full one, on middle and Boland blocks it out.
FOUR! Edged away! Length, around off. Boland gets the outside edge while looking to block. It runs past the diving third slip fielder for a boundary.
Beaten! On a length, just outside off. Boland sticks his bat out but it goes past the outside edge.
Too high this time with a bumper as Boland ducks under it. Wide called.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
A low full toss, on the pads. Lyon helps it to fine leg for a couple.
Full, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Broad fires a yorker, just outside off. Lyon fails to block it. Lyon asks Broad how did that miss the stumps?
Length ball, on off. Lyon gets forward to block it.
Very full again, on off. Lyon pushes it to mid off.
Full, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Full and outside off. Boland looks to drive but gets the outer half of the bat towards point.
Short of a length, on middle. Boland blocks it from the crease.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Scott Boland is the last man in for Australia.

OUT! BOWLED! Carey departs now! Well bowled by Woakes though. He bowls it on a length, right on the off pole. Carey leaves a bit of the gap between his bat and pads while looking to block it and that proves to be his undoing. The ball takes the inside edge and goes back onto hit the stumps.
Commentary.Howout: b Chris Woakes

Commentary.Commentary: Full, on off. Pushed to mid off by Carey.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.

SIX! Jeez! The GOAT has done it again! Short of a length, around off this time. Lyon pulls it way over the mid-wicket fence this time. He gives some catching practice to a few boys on the grass banks, but they drop it! 19 off 9 is Lyon.

SIX! HO HO! Ricky Ponting would be proud of that shot! Lyon has hit that so very well. A bumper on the body and Lyon hooks it way over the square leg fence. The fielders in the deep are mere spectators.
Length, on off. Swiped away to deep square leg by Carey for one.

FOUR! Just wide! Carey decides to take it on this time! Short and just down the leg side. Carey goes for the pull but gets some glove on it. Billings throws himself to his right but cannot get there. Boundary.
Bumper way down the leg side. Carey lets it go.
Carey hops up and taps it to point.
Good-length delivery, on off. Lyon pushes it to mid off.
Length delivery, around off. Lyon gets a bit forward to block it.
Nice and full, on middle. Lyon offers the full face of the bat and pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Lyon blocks it from the crease.
Clipped off the pads to deep square leg. This time Broad does the work neatly and gets a mild applause from the crowd.
Nice and full, on the pads. Worked towards deep mid-wicket. Broad runs in from the deep but fumbles while trying to pick the ball up. Two taken.
Chris Woakes (12-1-50-1) comes on to bowl for the first time on Day 2.
This goes way over Lyon's head as Wood digs it short.

SIX! The ploy almost works again! Almost being the key word as Lyon gets a maximum here! A bumper, on the body. The off-spinner pulls it in the air. There are two men in the deep. The fielders from deep square leg and deep mid-wicket converge but neither of them makes a full-hearted effort to get to the ball. Woakes from deep mid-wicket almost gets there but the ball sails over the fence.
Well played. Back of a length, around off. Carey sways away from the line of the ball and runs it to third man for one.
A bumper, on off. Carey ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Lyon pulls it away past mid-wicket for one.
Nathan Lyon walks out to bat now.

OUT! TAKEN! The trap has worked and Wood has been rewarded with a wicket here! “Put the cheese in the trap, in goes the mouse, off goes his head” the late great Bob Willis once said on air and this is exactly what happened. The ploy was simple. Have people back for the hook shot and have the relentless Mark Wood give the batters chin music. This is a short one, on middle. Cummins goes for the hook and hits it straight to deep square leg. Zak Crawley takes his third catch of the innings and Australia lose their skipper.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: Over the wicket and Broad lands this on a length, around off. Carey looks to punch it away but gets it off the inner half back to the bowler.
Takes him this time. Short and down the leg side. Cummins pulls it to fine leg for one.
On a length, around off. Cummins taps it towards cover.
Short, on off. Carey pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Nearly a drag on! Full and wide outside off. Carey goes at it with his hands but gets the inside edge. Luckily, the ball hits his pads and rolls away.
Nice and full, on off. Worked to mid-wicket.
Cummins ducks under this one and lets the keeper collect it.

Good bowling. Bumper, outside off. Carey looks to block but the ball balloons up and goes towards fine leg for one. That single brings up 250 for the Aussies. A good effort by them after losing 3 early wickets on this deck.
Back of a length, angling down the leg side. Carey leaves it alone.
Wood persisting with the short stuff. Carey backs away this time so Wood follows him with a short one. Carey looks to cut it away but is beaten.
Short again, on the body. Cummins awkwardly taps it past square leg for one. He was probably looking to duck at it at first but decided to play it in the end.
Wood bangs it in from 'round the wicket. Around middle but Cummins hops back to block it.
Short-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Carey stays back and punches it towards mid on.
Leg bye! Length ball, nipping back in from off. Cummins misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters sneak in a leg bye.
On a length, outside off. Pat Cummins leaves it alone.
Broad bowls a bouncer, around middle. Carey hangs back and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg and gives the strike back to his skipper.
Another good-length ball, on off. Carey is solid in his front foot defense.
Good-length ball, around off. Alex Carey defends it off the front foot.
Wood comes 'round the wicket and hurls a bumper, around middle. Cummins looks to leave it but the ball goes on with the angle and hits him on his chest guard.
Another short ball, but this time it is way down leg. Pat Cummins offers no shot to this one.
Good-length delivery, around off. Pat Cummins blocks it out.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Pat Cummins ducks underneath watchfully.
The skipper, Pat Cummins is in at number 9.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mark Wood strikes for England early on Day 2 and sends back Starc! Wood hurls a bumper, around middle. Starc looks to pull but the ball hurries onto him and it goes off the top edge, high in the air, just over the square leg fielder. Rory Burns at square leg backtracks and takes a good catch. Big wicket this for England as Starc could be very dangerous at this stage of the innings.
Commentary.Howout: c Rory Burns b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: Short of a length, around middle. Starc hangs back and blocks it out with ease.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mitchell Starc lunges forward and pushes it wide of mid off to collect a single.
Length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Mitchell Starc presses forward and eases it back past the bowler towards mid on. Broad dives to stop the ball but the ball goes past him.
Broad comes 'round the wicket now and hurls a fuller-length delivery, around off. Starc prods and pushes it towards mid off.
A bit fuller this time, well outside off. Mitchell Starc lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
Length ball, around leg. Alex Carey flicks it towards square leg and takes off for a quick run.
Another ball, around the rib-cage. Starc stays back and tucks it towards mid-wicket. Just 2 runs off the over!
Short of a length, around off. Mitchell Starc gets on top of the ball and blocks it with soft hands towards backward point.
Good-length ball, drifting onto the pad. Alex Carey glances it towards fine leg and collects a run.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex Carey keeps his bat inside the line of the ball and lets it through to the keeper.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Alex Carey ducks underneath.
Wood comes over the wicket this time to Starc and serves a full ball, around leg. Starc clips it off his pads towards the on side and gives the strike back to Carey.
Fuller-length ball, around off. Carey presses forward and pushes it to mid off.
On a length, just outside off and angling across the batter. Carey prods but shoulders his arms to this one.
A bit fuller in length, just outside off. Carey gets forward and drives it towards mid off.
On a length, around off. Alex Carey keeps it out watchfully.

Length ball, around off. Starc pushes it towards mid off and scampers through to the other end. The fielder at mid off scores a direct hit at the bowler's end but Starc was well home. First runs on Day 2 for the Aussies.
Broad starts with a wayward ball, down leg. Starc misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
It's going to be Stuart Broad (18-4-48-2) to steam in from the opposite end.
On a length, around off. Carey blocks it out solidly. Good start from Wood!

Top delivery! Wood serves a good-length delivery, around off and curling away late. Carey stays back to block but the ball zips past his outside edge. Wood appeals for a caught behind but the umpire says no. English skipper, Joe Root has a word with his mates regarding review but they decide to go against it.
Wood starts with a yorker, around the off pole. Carey gets his bat down in time to dig it out.

We are set to begin! A bit of cloud cover but there's sunshine as well. The players stride out to the middle. Alex Carey and Mitchell Starc are the overnight batters and Mark Wood to complete his unfinished over. Let's play...

Right now, the Aussies are in a purple patch as no matter what happens, there's someone who steps up and puts on a commanding display. When Warner, Khawaja and Smith fell with just 12 runs on the board, the hosts were reeling but the ever-dependable Marnus stayed strong and Head just came in and played a gem of an innings. It felt like he was never out of action as he rocketed to another century. Green too, stepped up big time and along with Head, has put the hosts ahead in the game. As many as 30 overs were lost on Day 1 and there are chances of rain on Day 2 as well. All we can do is hope to get a cracking day of cricketing action. Stay with us for further updates and the live action coming up soon.

Conditions were excellent for bowling on the first afternoon as there was ample cloud cover to aid the bowlers. The English bowlers did make the pink ball talk right from the get-go and Broad and Robinson reaped early rewards. It didn't last long though and the Aussies fought back hard and with Robinson not being fully fit, the English bowling was soon filled with cracks. After toiling for a long time, they did get wickets towards the end but won't be too pleased after getting such a good start in a match which is their last hope of getting a win in this series.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 2 of the fifth and final Ashes Test match between Australia and England at the Bellerive Oval. Well, the first day was cut short due to rain but it was certainly filled with action as the hosts made a roaring comeback after losing their top three really early on and have got themselves in a really promising position. The visitors will be looking to start Day 2 just like they started Day 1.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

The first session of Day 2 is an important one. If Carey along with the all-rounders manage to get a few handy stands, England will fall behind in the game. On the other hand, if England manage to take wickets early, they are right back into the contest. Do join us, the action will begin at 9 am IST (3:30 am GMT). Do join us for the same. Till then, Cheers!

The start though wasn’t the best for the hosts. They were 3 for 12 after England elected to bowl. They though couldn’t capitalise on the advantage as Labuschagne who was dropped early and Head steadied the ship with a 70-run stand but the former fell just before Dinner. Head and Green continued. The two played aggressively and added over 120 with Head scoring another ton. He though was dismissed immediately after that. Green too did not last for long as he too perished after getting to his milestones. Just as the momentum seemed like shifting in the final session, rain arrived and played spoilsport.

Well, the inevitable has happened! There was a slight chance in between as the rain stopped for a while but it came back and the umpires had enough of it. The day has been called off. We had just short of 60 overs of play on Day 1 but it was an exuberating day of cricket. In the end one has to say, it is the Australians who will be the happier of the two sides.
UPDATE - 4:15 pm IST (10:45 am GMT) - It has started raining now at Hobart. It looks like, this might be the end of the day's play as chances are looking bleak now.

UPDATE - 4 pm IST (10:30 am GMT) - Not quite sure why the covers are still on. It is not even raining now and neither it was that heavy to stop the play firstly, only the umpire has the umbrella open in the whole ground. Still waiting for any official comment. Stay tuned.

UPDATE - 3:38 pm IST (10:08 am GMT) - There is a slight drizzle at the moment, the umpires did get together to have a chat but they are willing to continue. Just as we write that, they got together again and have decided to go off. The covers are called on. The crowd is not happy and so aren't the players. It is a very light drizzle. Let us hope it passes away quickly. Till then though you can catch all the action from the India game. The hosts need another 55 runs and have just lost Keegan Petersen. India do have an opening but can they make use of it? Switch tabs to find out.
Another bouncer from Wood, Carey lets it through.
Short ball, on middle. Carey ducks under it. Some sawdust spread to the bowler's landing area.
FOUR! Good shot! A short ball, outside off. Carey hops and slashes it over point for a boundary. Good reflexes from the umpire as he sits under it quickly.
Slower ball but continues to serve it outside off. Easy leave for Starc.
Outside off again, Left alone.
Full ball, just outside off. Starc shoulders arms to it.
Full and slanting outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on off. Blocked out by Starc.
On a length, on the hips, tucked away to square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Wood gets the wicket, he was not giving any freebie in this over. He was bowling with fire and pace. Excellent execution also, changes and comes in around the wicket. serves a short ball, on middle. Cameron Green looks to pull but it takes the top edge towards deep mid-wicket where Zak Crawley takes a good catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, on middle. Green tucks it to short square leg. Aggressive bowling from Mark Wood.
Short but slanting down the leg side. Green evades it.
Lovely bowling! Targets the body with yet another bumper. Green stands tall and blocks it out.
Angles it from around the wicket on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for one.
Serves a short ball, just outside off. Carey arcs back and sways away from the line. Good bumper.
Full ball, on off, driven nicely but finds cover.
FOUR! Pierces through the gap! A full ball, outside off. Green drives it, beats the diving fielder and it races away to the fence.
Touch fuller, on middle. Green stays back and defends it to the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Green taps it to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Green leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Carey looks t play it late but gets an inside edge past the stumps and to the leg side. Single.
A dot to end! On off, this is pushed to covers.
A short one and on the body, Green evades it well.
A short one and on the body, Green ducks under it.
FOUR! Another lovely stroke! Classy! Shorter and on off, once again Green stands tall and gets on top of the bounce. He guides it through point for a boundary.
Cuts Green into half! Shorter and outside off, this lands and comes back in. Green looks to defend but it goes in between bat and body and to the keeper. It just about got to the keeper.
On middle, Green stays back and blocks.
Another length delivery to end, it is outside off, Carey shoulders arms to this one.
Length and outside off, Carey does not fiddle with it.
Good length and on off, Carey defends.
Two more! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for two.
On the stumps, Carey leans forward and keeps it out.
On middle, Carey plays it back to the bowler.
Just not been at his best! Now slips one down the leg side, Green misses the flick.

FOUR! That was class personified! Wow! Beautiful! Shorter and on off, Green stands tall, gets on top of the bounce and pushes it past the cover region for a boundary. Second boundary in the over, Wood continues to leak runs.
Corrects his line and bowls it on a length and around off, defended.
FOUR! Errs in line and pays the price! This is full and on middle, Green walks across and clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Yet again on middle, Green plays it back to the bowler.
Wood begins well! He has been expensive so far but needs to do well now. He lands it on a length and around off, defended.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Mark Wood.
On middle, Carey plays it back to the bowler.
Another one on a length and around off, Carey plays it right under his eyes.
Solid! On a good length and on off, Carey keeps it out.
First run of the session! Fuller and on middle, Green strokes it wide of mid on and gets to the other end.
Length and outside off now, left alone well.
Starts off with one from wide of the crease and angles it into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
We are back for the final session. Cameron Green and Alex Carey stride out to continue their innings. Stuart Broad to start with the ball.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

England on the other hand, have let the advantage slip they had after Dinner. Their bowlers were quite poor in this session to be honest. They lacked control, there were far too many boundary balls. Not only that, Root was a tad defensive with his tactics as he probably wasn't as attacking as he should have been. They need to comeback strongly though after the break or this day could belong to the hosts after being 12 for 3. An important session awaits. Stay tuned as the final session will resume at 3 pm IST (9:30 am GMT).

What a session for Australia and from being behind the game, they are now well and truly in control of it. The key for them was the rate they scored at, they have managed over 120 runs and lost just one wicket. Both Green and Head came out and tried to be positive from the word go and it came off. They scored freely and the two added a massive 121-run stand. Head was the mainstay, he also got his ton up but fell on the next ball. Green though has notched up his half ton and will be wishing to get to his ton. Carey has got through the nervy period before the break and would be eager to cash in now. One more partnership and the Aussies will have a good first innings score.

Ohh...a scare for Carey on the last ball of the session! A flatter and quicker delivery angled into middle from 'round the wicket. Carey looks to push this towards the off side off the back foot. He gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball rolls just away from stumps towards short fine leg. Australia are 215/5 at Tea on Day 1.
A  fuller delivery on middle. carely solidly blocks it.
Drifts down the leg side this time Root. Green clips it fine towards long leg for three runs. Good running.
Another flatter delivery on off. Green stays deep in his crease and blocks it.
A flatter delivery on middle. Green blocks it solidly.
Slightly shorter and turning into middle and leg. Green works it to square leg.
Nice stroke but straight to the fielder. Slightly fuller on off. Carey leans forward and drives it straight to mid off.
Woakes hit the length hard again and lands this on off. Carey defends this solidly off the front foot.
Back of a length, around off again. Carey decides to leave it alone.
Pulls his length back and bowls this around off, Carey watches it till the end and lets it go.
Fuller this time on middle. Carey works it towards mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Carey blocks this solidly off the front foot.
FOUR! Classy shot! Root serves this fuller outside off. Green leans forward and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary. Superb shot!
Fuller delivery outside off. Carey drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Pushed quicker on off. Carey defends this off the front foot towards the off side.

Fifty for Green! A very calm and measured innings! Some really beautiful strokes so far in this knock. He was short of runs but Australia will hope this is the start of something. His third Test fifty. He has gone along things really nicely. A ton is on the offer here. He gets there by pushing it towards cover and getting to the other end.
Slightly shorter outside off. Green goes deep in his crease and pushes it to backward point for a couple.
A  flatter ball, on off. Green blocks it out.
A  length delivery on off. Carey blocks it out solidly.
Alex Carey walks out to the middle.

OUT! TAKEN! Oh...Head departs on the very next ball after getting to the century! A fuller delivery on middle. Head looks to work it away towards the on side but gets the leading edge again. This time the ball travels towards mid on and Ollie Robinson there takes a good catch. So Head departs and this dangerous partnership is finally broken.  Head walks back after another brilliant knock. His team was under the pump when he walked out to the middle and has managed to take his team to a much better position with his counter-attacking century. Can England capitalize on this breakthrough? They need a couple of quick wickets to get back into this game.
Commentary.Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Chris Woakes

Commentary.Commentary: 100 for Travis Head! What a knock, a knock he will probably never forget! Absolutely stunning. Walked out when his team was 3 down for hardly anything and has single-handedly taken his side to safer shores on a wicket which can be considered as a really tough wicket to bat on. His second ton in this year's Ashes but this one is surely better than the last one. An innings full of class and some brilliant stroke making. He gets there in an edgy manner but he really won't care. It is a short ball outside off, Head looks to cut but this goes off the underedge down towards third man. The batters take two. The people in the ground are on their feet applauding the effort. He takes the helmet off and soaks it in. He has a chance to make it a big ton now.
Heart in the mouth moment! A leading edge but safe! A fuller delivery on middle. Head looks to work it away towards the on side but gets a leading edge towards mid on. Luckily for him it falls short.
The wait continues! A fuller delivery on middle. Head calmly defends this back to the bowler.
Woakes bowls this fuller on off. Green drives it to mid off and gets a quick single. Here we go, Head on 99. Can he get a hundred off the next ball?
Dot ball! He will have to wait for his century! A fuller delivery on off. Head drives it to the cover fielder.
Quicker and flatter on off. Green easily knocks it to long on for a single.
Angled into middle again. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Root fires this on quicker on middle. Head pushes it to mid on.
Darted on the pads. Green works it to mid-wicket and another easy single taken.
Flatter on middle and angling in from 'round the wicket. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, on middle. Green defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, fuller delivery, Green pushes it to covers.
BEATEN! Hint of away swing, on a length and outside off. Green has a poke at it but misses.
Fuller ball, outside off. Green pushes it to covers.
On a length, on off. Head hits it to deep point for one more.
FOUR! Travis Head moves to 96! A length ball, angling on the pads. Head whips it aerially over square leg for a boundary.
Chris Woakes (9.0-0-42-0) is back into the attack.
Another short ball, on middle. Green defends this off the back foot.
On middle, this is short. Green rocks back and blocks it out.
Darted on the pads, this is hit through square leg for a single.
Flatter and on off. Kept out.
Quick single! This is good running! Full ball, on off. Green pushes it to mid off and calls for a quick single, Makes it to the other end on time.
Tossed up, on off, this is pushed through covers for a single.
This is on a length, outside off, slower ball as well. Green is touch early as he looks to push, he hits it towards covers.
Much better! Fuller and on off, pushed to mid off.
This is again outside off stump. Green covers his off stump and lets it through.
Length ball, way outside off. Green leaves it alone.
Length and on off. Head punches it to sweeper cover for a single. He moves into the 90s.
Length and on middle. Head stays back and blocks it out.
Shorter and on middle. Green blocks it off the back foot. Not much turn to offer for Joe Root.
Flatter and on leg. Green pushes it off the inner half to the leg side.
On middle, Green comes down the track to keep it out.
Slightly short on off. Green gets on the back foot to defend it.
Fuller and on middle. Blocked on the leg side.
Tossed up, turning in, on middle, flicked to square leg.
Length and on middle. Blocked out.
Slower ball, on off, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Stuart Broad seems to have some problem with the ball. The umpire says it is good to continue and Stuart Broad obliges.
This one comes with the angle, on a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but gets cramped for the room lately.
Full and on off, driven nicely but straight to covers.
FOUR! Timing! A full ball, outside off. Head caresses it through covers and it races away to the fence. Some glorious drives from Travis Head in this innings.
Length and angling on off. Blocked out.
Slower in the air on middle. Head works it wide of mid on for a single.
Pushed through quicker outside off. Head looks to cut it but misses.
100 runs partnership comes up! A fuller delivery that is turning back in. Green works it to square leg for a single. Superb partnership between these two.
A fuller delivery on middle. Green works it to mid-wicket.
THREE BYES! A flatter delivery down the leg side. Head looks to clip it away but misses. Sam Billings fails to collect it cleanly too and the batters run three byes towards long leg.
Fuller on middle. Head skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Green defends it off the back foot solidly.
FOUR! Glorious shot! An overpitched delivery on off. Green plants his front foot forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Slightly fuller on off. Head drives it wide of mid off for a single.

FOUR! What a shot! He is looking in supreme touch here! Back of a length, around off. Head stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary, He is poicking the length so quickly that nothing is working against him.
On a length, on middle. Green works it to backward square leg for a single.
Broad starts with a full delivery outside off. Green is nicely forward to that one and drives it to covers. The fielder there stops it.
Stuart Broad is back into the attack.
Head picks the length quickly again. This is back of a length, on off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length, on middle. Head works it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Back of a length, outside off. Green plays away from his body and gets a thick outside edge. Te ball goes through backward point region and the batters run three before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length again, around off. Head pushes it to third man for a single.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Head looks to clip it but misses.

FOUR! Edge but boundary for Head! Back of a length, around off. Head is cramped for room but still goes for a back foot punch. He gets a thick outside edge and ball flies through the vacant slip corridor for a boundary. Just one slip in place.
Mark Wood is back into the attack.
Fires it on off, Green stays back and defends.
Two more! Slightly fuller and on off, Green pushes it through covers for two.
Angled into the pads, Head works it through mid-wicket for one.
Runs continue to come! Head comes down the track and also makes room. He hits it through covers for two.
Slightly shorter in length, Head pushes it to covers.
Flatter and on middle, Head pushes it back to the bowler.

Drinks! Australia are just marching along quite nicely here in the second session. English bowlers have bowled well in patches but both these batters Green and Head have looked quite comfortable out there in the middle. Ollie Robinson doesn't look 100 percent fit and that has hurt England here. England need a wicket quickly, otherwise the game can drift away from them quite easily if these two get going.
Another productive over for Australia! The last ball is played late and towards point for one.
Timed well again but finds mid off. Fuller and on off, it is hit right off the middle but to the fielder at mid off.

FOUR! Not sure if the wicket has eased off or the batting is just too good at the moment! This is a back of a length delivery on off, Head goes back and pushes it through covers. This one races away to the fence.
And another single! On the pads, Green nudges it on the leg side. There is no pressure from England at the moment. They are unable to build any kind of pressure we should say.
Goes fuller and around off, Head pushes it wide of mid off for one more. The two look at ease for now. Runs are also ciming quite easily.
On middle, Green works it through mid-wicket for one.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through square leg. The man at deep mid-wicket, runs to his right, dives and keeps it down to three.
On off, kept out.
On middle, Green pushes it back to the bowler.
On the pads, Head looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On off, Green defends.
On off, Head plays it late and on the off side, he wants a run but is sent back.
Keeps it behind a length and on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
Another back of a length ball, Head stays back and defends.
Length again and on off, this one jags back in. It is pushed to mid off.
On off, Head gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, Green strokes it wide of mid off for one.
Stuart Broad (9.0-4-15-2) is back into the attack.
This is quicker and on middle, skids through. Head gets his bat down in time and pushes it to covers.
On off, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, Head works it to mid on.
Fuller and on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, Green looks to drop and on the off side but Head sends him back.
On off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Another length delivery on off. Green defends it comfortably yet again. Woakes is not getting much movement out there.
A length ball, on off with perfect seam position. Green is solid in his defence again.
A length ball, on off. Head defends it off the outer half of his blade to point. He gets a single.
Overpitched on off. Green works it through mid-wicket with his wrists. The fielder there runs behind it and saves a run for his team with a dive near the fence. Three runs taken.
A length ball, on off. Green is solid in his front foot defence.
Full delivery around leg. Head flicks it to deep square leg for a single. An easy single given again. Poor cricket from England.
Darted on middle and leg. Head works it to deep mid-wicket for a single. He uses his wrists to a good effect.
Easy single there. A fuller delivery on off. Green pushes it to long on and gets a single.
Slower in the air on off. Green defends this off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on off. Head drives it to long off for a single.
Ohh..alomost drags it on! A fuller deliver on off. Head looks to drive but gets the inside edge onto his pads and ball rolls just away from the stumps.
A fuller delivery on off. Green drives it to covers and gets a single.
Joe Root is into the attack now.
Well fielded! Shorter in length and outside off, Head cuts, it goes towards point. The fielder there dives to his right and stops it well.
On the off pole, drags his length back too. Kept out.
Wood changes the angle, goes around the wicket and bowls it full and on off, this is driven to covers.
FOUR! Hammered! That is put away with disdain! Fuller and on off, Head throws the kitchen sink at it, he smashes it wide of mid off and into the fence.
Back of a length and on off, Head pushes it to covers.

FOUR! Fifty for Head! Back in the side and back amongst the runs. Another important knock. Came out in tough conditions, his side was in trouble, weathered the storm early and is now cashing in. A big score is on the offer here. He gets a gift to get to the milestone. On the pads, this is worked down to the fine leg fence.
A dot to end! Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid on.
Looks to bowl a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss, it is pushed to mid off for one.
Some issue with the landing area. Sawdust has been spread...
Back of a length and on off, Head hops and guides it to point.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through square leg for one.
On the pads, Head flicks it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Angled into the pads, Green works it through mid-wicket for one.
This one takes off! On a length and on off, extra bounce. Head does well to play it by taking a hand off the handle. A good over by Woakes, except for that boundary ball, he was on the money.
A little too straight, comes back in. Head looks to flick but misses to get hit above the knee roll.
On the fuller side and on middle, Head strokes it back to the bowler.
Good comeback! The last one was bowled a touch wide. This time he lands it on off and gets it to shape away. Head is beaten as he tries to block.
FOUR! Another superb shot from Head! Back of a length, around off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through point for a boundary. He is in great touch out here.
Back of a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but misses. He is not shying away from playing his shots.

FOUR! Good bowling but is played well by Green! Back of a length, around off. Green stays back and pushes at it with soft hands. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade a little and runs through the gully region for a boundary.
Wood goes fuller and Head drives it past mid off. Stokes runs behind it and cuts it off before the batters run three.
Good running there. Back of a length, on off. Green pushes it off the back foot to covers and takes a quick single.
Back of a length on off at 142 clicks. Green rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Wood goes short again on off. Green is upto the task and ducks under it.
Another shorter length delivery angled into the body of Travis Head. He plays it awkwardly towards the on side for a single. This is a better length against Head.
Woakes goes fuller on off. Green drives it firmly back to the bowler.
Runs for Australia. A length ball, around off. Green plays it late and opens the face of his blade. He gets it through backward point for a couple.
Pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Green leaves it alone.
He goes fuller now. Green drives this off the front foot to covers. This is a better length from Woakes.
Woakes hits the length hard this time on off. Green is solid in his defence.
Woakes starts with bowling in that channel around off. Green lets it go.
Chris Woakes is back into the attack.
100 up for Australia! A length ball, on off. Green gets across and works it to mid-wicket for another single.
A slightly fuller delivery outside off. Head plays it from his crease towards covers and gets a single. He did well to get a bat on it.
Angled into middle and leg this time. Green works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Play and a miss this time! A shorter length delivery outside off. Wood gets some extra bounce and Green misses his cut shot.
Slightly fuller outside off by Wood. Green plants his front foot forward and then decides to let it go.
Wood is bowling with good steam here. He lands it on a length, outside off. Gree leaves it alone as he covers his off pole.
A good-length delivery outside off. Head leaves it alone.
A length ball, on off. Head blocks it out this time towards the off side.
FOUR! Head is in no mood to play cautiously here! A fuller delivery on leg. Another medium pace delivery. Head whips this off his legs towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Pulls his length back a little on middle. Green works it to backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! slightly fuller on off. Green plants his front foot forward and drives it left of mid off for a boundary. Nice timing there.
A gentle loosener from Ollie Robinson. He lands it on a length, outside off. Green leaves it alone.
Who will bowl now? It is Ollie Robinson.
Wood goes a tad fuller this time on middle. Head drives it past mid on and gets a couple. Good start from Wood to this second session.
Another slightly shorter length delivery on off. Head defends this off the back foot.
Back of a length, on off. Head hops and blocks it onto the turf.
Ouch! This hits Head on his helmet! A nasty pacy short ball on middle. Head is surprised by the bounce and pace and takes his eyes off the ball. He gets hit on the helmet but not much damage done.
A length ball, on off. Green drives it to cover-point and gets a single. First run after Dinner.
Wood starts with a good-length delivery outside off. Green leaves it alone comfortably. He would like to get little closer to the stumps.
We are back for the second session. Travis Head and Cameron Green to resume their innings. Mark Wood to initiate this session. Let's play ...
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

England will love more of the same. They would want to keep picking wickets and now will also try to make run scoring difficult. Australia on the other hand, need a partnership. Head has got his eye in and Green is due. They need the two to bat for long. Can they do so? We will find out. Join us for the second session at 12:40 pm IST (7:10 am GMT).

An excellent session for England, especially after the wicket of Labuschagne, they will be mighty pleased with how things went about in this session after electing to bowl. They started with a bang, they got three in no time. Could have easily had 4 had they not dropped Labuschagne. Travis Head and Marnus Labuschagne then began a counter-attack. The two added 71 in no time and it seemed like all the good work from the English at the start will fade away courtesy the two. Broad though got rid of Marnus right towards the end of the session in a very bizarre manner to tilt the tide back into his side's favor.
Another solid block from Travis Head. This was on a length and on off. That will be Dinner on Day 1.
On middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, angling outside off, late swing there as well. Head leaves it alone.
Angles a length ball, on middle, tucked away to square leg for one more.
Touch fuller, straight on middle. Green defends it off the front foot.
On middle, on a length. Blocked on the leg side.
Green is off the mark! A length ball, on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single. Excellent over for England, they are on back on top at the verge of Dinner.
Full ball, almost a yorker, on off. Green gets his bat down in time and blocks it.
Length again, outside off. Green shoulders arms to it.
Five slips in place now.
Length ball, outside off. Green leaves this wayward delivery.
Full ball, outside off, Green pushes it to covers.
Cameron Green walks in at number 6.

OUT! TIMBER! What just happened there! That looked ugly! Marnus Labuschagne has been cleaned up around his legs but that dismissal just seemed ugly. Just like always, he shuffles across, gets over to the off pole. Broad goes full and straight on middle, Marnus Labuschagne gets into a tangle as he tries to clip it on the leg side. In the end, loses his balance, falls onto the ground. Misses the ball by a long way and the ball shatters the stumps behind. Broad is elated and Marnus Labuschagne is not sure about what just happened. It was a really good innings till it lasted but Australia needed him to go on. Replays actually shows he just planted his front foot way too across and hence, lost balance. Very unusual from Marnus Labuschagne. Really not sure what he just did there. England now back on top.
Commentary.Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Slightly shorter and on off, Head looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Yet again attacks the stumps and on off, Head blocks.
Good length again and on off, Head plays it late and on the off side.
FOUR! That squirts off the outer half! Fuller and on off, shapes away late. Head looks to drive, this goes off the outside edge past point and into the boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.
There seems to be a problem with the seam of the ball. The box full of balls comes out and England have been given a different cherry now.
A really good over from Broad! Bowled with a lot of fire. The last ball though is a harmless one, outside off, easy leave.
Well played! Good length and on off, Labuschagne stays back and blocks.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Solid now! This time Marnus Labuschagne holds his ground and plays this length ball to point.

Broad did not like that at all! Marnus Labuschagne comes down the track, he looks to hit it through the off side but gets an underedge back to the bowler. Broad has a shy at the keeper's end but hits ML by mistake. It was more of a message from Broad that stay back.
And again, walks right across, this time the length is shorter and hence, he works it all along the ground through mid-wicket for two. Marnus Labuschagne is in the mood here.
Just outside off, Head covers his off pole and lets it go.
Fuller and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it through square leg for one.

FOUR! What a shot by Marnus Labuschagne! A shot of authority and a player who is high on confidence right now. He walks right across and then whips this delivery on off over mid-wicket for a boundary. Absolutely no respect shown for Woakes there. Marnus Labuschagne into the 40s now.
Fuller this time and on off, Head goes hard at it, mistimes it towards mid off for one.
Does get this one to shape back in a touch from outside off, not enough though to make the batter play.
On the fuller side and on off, Head strokes it back to the bowler. The swing and movement seems to have gone now.
Another length delivery outside off and another leave from Marnus Labuschagne. Broad bowls this on a length and tad wider outside off. Marnus Labuschagne is happy to let it go.
A length delivery outside off and nipping in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms again.
A good-length delivery around off. Marnus Labuschagne covers his off pole and lets it go.

A bit fuller delivery on off. Head is back on the delivery he should have been forward and ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads. The batters run a quick single as the ball rolls towards the on side. Good running.
A length delivery outside off. Head lets it go this time.
Broad drifts it on the leg stump. Head works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Wood is leaking runs so England go back to the experience Stuart Broad.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it back to the bowler. Chris Woakes stops it and is looking visibly frustrated.
This is better from Chris Woakes! A good-length delivery around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball seams away and hits him on the back leg.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off solidy this time.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Marnus Labuschagne looks to clip it but misses.
Shorter length on middle this time. Head pulls it to deep mid-wicket and the batters run three again. This is poor bowling and great running by the batters.
Woakes bowls this on a length, outside off. Head looks to cut it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
FOUR! Another cracking shot! Wood has been poor to say the least today! Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary. Superb batting.
A length ball, on off. Head pushes it to covers with soft hands and gets a single.

Another nice shot but Ben Stokes saves a boundary with a slide near the fence! A fuller delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne drives it past mid on and the ball almost races away for a boundary before Stokes cuts it off. Three runs taken.
FOUR! Short ball and punished by Marnus Labuschagne! Wood bowls this short on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls this uppishly towards deep square leg and gets another boundary.
Nice timing again by Head! Back of a length, outside off. Head rides the bounce and punches it through covers. Pope runs behind it and saves a run for his team. Three runs taken.
A length ball, outside off. Head lets it go comfortably.
A good-length delivery outside off. Marnus Labuschagne covers his off pole and leaves it.
FOUR! Runs are flowing now! A fuller delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for another boundary. 50 up for Australia now.

This time an edge but soft hand there from Marnus Labuschagne. A good-length delivery around off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward to defend but gets a thick edge and just short of the third slip fielder.
A good-length delivery outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

In the air...but safe! Woakes pulls his length back this time and bowls this around off. Head looks to pull but completely miscues it. The ball goes high in the air and falls in a vacant area towards mid off. A single taken.
FOUR! Woakes is greeted with a boundary! A fulller delivery outside off. Head leans forward and drives it through cover-point for a boundary.
Chris Woakes is into the attack.
FOUR! Width on offer! Good over for Australia, 11 coming off it! Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes and slaps it through point for a boundary.
Angles it on the pads. Head hops and wrists it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Touch fuller, around off. Head leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles and nudges it to square leg for a single.
Full again, on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an outside edge to gully. Got hurried up there.
Full ball, outside off. Head drives it to mid off. The fielder there half-stops and a single is taken.
This one comes back in very late, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Again down the leg side. Labuschagne misses his flick.
That whizzed past the leg stump! Length ball, angling down the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne steps across and looks to flick but misses.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
On the pads, this is tucked to square leg for a single.
Length ball, angling across outside off. Head shoulders arms to it.

Drinks! This has been a superb start for England. There is help from the surface for them and they have taken full advantage of it. Three wickets down in the first hour and England need to make this count now. Australia have Head and Marnus Labuschagne in the middle and will be hoping that they go to Lunch without further damage. Another riveting passage of Test cricket coming up.
Length ball, way outside off. Easy leave for Labuschagne.
FOUR! Anything overpitched and Marnus Labuschagne is putting it away! Full and on middle. This is whipped through square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone by Marnus.
On a length, around off. Head looks to cut but this is too close to the body. It goes off the under edge, past the off stump and to square leg. One.
Goes wide of the crease and slants it on a length, on middle. Head blocks it out.
Full ball, outside off, this is pushed on the off side.
Here is the first change of the morning. Mark Wood is into the attack now.
A length ball, angling on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. Half-hearted appeal but this was going down.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Good leave! This one comes back in, Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne covers his off stump and lets it through.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! Full again, around off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it uppishly and wide of the diving cover fielder for a boundary.
BEATEN AGAIN! Lovely bowling from Ollie Robinson so far! Keeping it tight by serving it in the channel! This is on a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but misses.
Length and on off. Head tucks it off the back foot through square leg for three runs. He is off the mark.
FOUR! Good shot! This will release some pressure! A rare loosener from Broad. Pitches it up, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Touch fuller, outside off, it straightens off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne defends inside the line of the ball and gets beaten.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer from Broad, steep bounce as well. Marnus Labuschagne sits under it. Good carry for the keeper as well.
This one angles in from outside off, fuller. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Length and on the pads, this is flicked to square leg.
Travis Head is the next batter in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! What a start for England! Crawley takes the catch, he put one down before but holds onto this one. Smith walks back for a duck! This is slightly shorter than a length, around off. Again Steven Smith shuffles way across and tries to block it but this moves away a bit and takes the outside edge. It goes to Zak Crawley at second slip who takes a low catch. Perfect start for England. Yet another low score for Steven Smith.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: Length and on off. Steven Smith comes right across and misses his flick. It takes the thigh guard and goes to square leg.
Angles it on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne plays it late and tucks it through square leg for a single.
A length ball, around off, it lands and jags back in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne leaves but this comes back in and hits him high on the pads.
FOUR! First boundary and Marnus Labuschagne is off the mark! Too straight from Ollie Robinson, on the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Steven Smith walks in at number 4.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Khawaja now goes and England have both the openers back in the hut very cheaply. Two centuries in the last game but falls for a single digit score here. Broad also has one now. Hard hands once again. This is on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Khawaja pushes at it with hard hands, he plays it well ahead of his body. Not what you want to do in seaming conditions. It goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Root at first slip. Australia in trouble here. England could have easily had three but this is a superb start for them.
Commentary.Howout: c Joe Root b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: That goes into the fence but dead ball signaled. On the pads, Khawaja leaves it alone. It hits the pad and goes down to the fine leg fence. Dead ball signaled as no shot was offered.
Yet another delivery, just outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to this one.
Just outside off, Khawaja lets it be.

This is relentless stuff from the two opening bowlers. Just attacking the stumps on almost every delivery, testing the batter continously. Length and on middle, this lands and then moves away. Khawaja hangs back and tries to put bat on ball. This time it straightens and hits high on the pad.
Broad now goes fuller, gets this one to hold its line. Khawaja looks to drive but it goes off the outer half to point.
A leave to end a superb over by Ollie Robinson! Quality stuff from the pacer, should have had a wicket. Outside off, Marnus lets it be.
Is that an edge? No, it is bat hitting pad! On off, this lands and then shapes away again. Labuschagne looks to block. There is a noise as the ball passes the bat. Half an appeal but turned down.

EDGED AND PUT DOWN! Crawley puts down what was not his catch. A life for the number 1 Test batter in the world. Another lovely nut from Ollie Robinson. This is on a length and around off, it lands and then moves away. Labuschagne plays the original trajectory but the ball takes the outside edge. It goes between first slip and second who are standing a little too close. It is actually Root's catch as it seems to be going straight to him. Crawley dives to his left but does not hang on. This can prove costly.
Solid! This will make Labuschagne feel good! On a length and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.

This is even better! Outstanding stuff. Ollie Robinson has his tail up here! Gets it to go the other way. Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Marnus Labuschagne comes forward to block but is beaten.

That was close! A good leave in the end! Outside off, tails back in. Marnus Labuschagne covers his off pole and lets it be. It goes just past the off pole. Do not think he expected it to come back that much.
Broad pulls his length back a little this time. He lands it on a length, on off. Usman Khawaja is right behind it to block it.
A fuller delivery again but this time down the leg side. Usman Khawaja looks to flick it but misses.
Another full delivery, this time on middle. Usman Khawaja drives this past mid on and gets another couple of runs. Broad is looking for some swing out there.
This is fuller and Usman Khawaja goes for a drive. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes past gully for a couple.
Broad gets his line right this time and lands this on a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Broad bowls this down the leg side. Usman Khawaja looks to clip it but it is way down the leg side.
Marnus Labuschagne walks in at number 3.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Just as I write that, Ollie Robinson strikes! England do get an early breakthrough. Commentator's curse? Maybe. This is a lovely delivery. Perfect line and length. It is just ahead of a good length ball which means it draws the batter forward. Lands and moves away. It takes the outside edge of Warner's bat as he looks to defend and goes into the hands of Crawley at third slip. Ollie Robinson is delighted. Warner walks back for a duck. Warner actually put in a small stride forward. He ended up poking at the delivery. He was more worried about the back of a length ball and hence, did not put in a big stride which cost him his wicket. This was quite similar to the way Wood set him up in the previous game.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: On middle, Warner lunges and defends. The openers have done well so far. Worrying signs for England though that they have not got a wicket yet. The good thing is they have not gone for a lot of runs.
Just outside off, Warner does not fiddle with it.
Good length and on off, Warner plays it to covers.
This lands just outside leg, holds its line. Warner stays back and tries to block but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Outside off, moving away. Warner watches it go to the keeper. A lot of patience shown by the Aussie openers so far and rightly so. They need to get past this tough phase.
BEAUTY! Gets this to move away nicely. Fuller, just behind a driving length. Khawaja is tempted into a drive. The ball though lands and then moves away. Beats the outside edge.
On middle, Khawaja stays back and blocks.
A little too straight, Warner looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. Leg bye taken. Warner is yet to get off the mark.
Yet again on the fuller side, no movement in the air, Warner plays it to mid on.
Down the leg side this time, Warner looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
On middle, slightly fuller, this is flicked but to mid-wicket.
Better! A near perfect delivery. It lands on off and then moves away. Squares Khawaja up as he tries to block. It whizzes past the outside edge.

Good nut! Need to start it a little straighter, this lands just outside off, it pitches and moves away. Khawaja is beaten as he tires to defend. There was quite some distance between the edge and the ball.
Another one outside off, Khawaja does not fiddle with it.
Cramps the batter for room by bowling it on his body. Khawaja looks to flick but misses to get hit on the body.
Just outside off, angling away. Khawaja moves across and lets it be.
Very stylish but for no runs! Fuller and on middle, Khawaja flicks but to mid-wicket.
Another maiden for Broad! England have started well. Length and on off, Warner plays it to point.
Goes back to bowling it on a length and outside off, left alone.
Testing stuff from Broad here! Now goes for the yorker, looks to catch Warner by surprise. David gets his bat down and jams it out.

Close! Not sure why Broad was appealing there! Length and on off, this one skids through. Warner is a touch late in getting his bat down. It hits the underedge and bounces just in front of the stumps and then goes over it.
Loose! Short and wide outside off, Warner slashes well away from his body, gets beaten. Too early probably to play that shot.
Just outside off, Warner covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Two from Robinson's first then! Length and just outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to this one.
Now drags his length back and bowls it on middle, no movement this time, Khawaja stays back and plays it back to the bowler.

Australia and Usman Khawaja are underway! Full and on middle, Khawaja clips it through square leg and takes two. Robinson went a little too full there and it was easy pickings for a man who scored two tons in the last game.
On middle, this time Khawaja gets right behind the line of the delivery and keeps it out.

Another good delivery! Length and on off, this one also lands and moves away. Khawaja is once again beaten as he tries to block. Robinson has got to get the ball moving off the wicket in his first two deliveries, he has started off well here.
That is a beauty to begin with by Ollie Robinson! This is on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Usman Khawaja is beaten as he tries to block.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Ollie Robinson.

A maiden then to begin with by Broad! On off, this is pushed to covers. So not a lot of movement for the pacer but we saw one ball zip through and the other just hold in the surface in the first over.
Length agian and on off, this lands and moves away. It also seems like it stuck in the surface, it just about gets to Sam Billings.
Good delivery! Broad goes fuller, enticing the batter to drive. Warner does go for it, this one comes back in a little, it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Another one on a length and just outside off, Warner covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Slightly fuller this time and on middle, Warner defends it nicely.

Some action straightaway! A huge appeal but turned down! A little too high probably. Broad lands this outside off, it is on a length. He usually takes the ball away from around the wicket but this time gets it to  jag back in. Warner makes a leave probably thinking it would move away. He gets hit high on the pads. An appeal from the slip cordon and Broad too who is down on the ground. Turned down. Broad signals it is too high.

We are all set for the action. The players of England stride out to the middle. Usman Khawaja and David Warner are the openers for Australia. Stuart Broad to start the proceedings. Three slips and a gully. Here we go ...

UPDATE - Revised timings - 10 am IST (4:30 am GMT) - 12 pm IST (6:30 am GMT) (First session), 12:40 pm IST (7:10 am GMT) - 2:40 pm IST (9:10 am GMT) (Second session), 3 pm IST (9:30 am GMT) - 5 pm IST (11:30 am GMT) (Third session).

Pat Cummins, the skipper of Australia, says that they would have bowled first as well looking at the conditions but it is not much of a problem. He adds that the final day at SCG was fun and that is why Test cricket is much exciting to play. He mentions that it is tough on Harris to miss out but Usman Khawaja deserves his chance after the performance in the last game. He adds that there is big history to this ground and it is great to play here.

Joe Root, the skipper of England, says that they will bowl first. He adds it is obvious after looking at the pitch and overhead conditions. He mentions that it has been frustrating to lose players along the way and it has been this way since the pandemic. He adds that it was important to get a draw in the last game and hopes that they can build on it.

England (Playing XI) - Rory Burns (In for Haseeb Hameed), Zak Crawley, Dawid Malan, Joe Root (C), Ben Stokes, Ollie Pope (In for Jonny Bairstow), Sam Billings (WK) (In for Jos Buttler), Chris Woakes (In for James Anderson), Ollie Robinson (In for Jack Leach), Mark Wood, Stuart Broad.

Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head (In for Marcus Harris), Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Mitchell Starc, Scott Boland, Nathan Lyon.
TOSS - England have won the toss and elected to BOWL first.
Update - 0911 IST (0340 GMT) - We have some good news! The covers are off and we have a time as well. TOSS WILL TAKE PLACE AT 0930 IST and (0400 GMT) which is 20 minutes from now. Hurray!!!

Well, the drizzle continues to fall and the TOSS HAS BEEN DELAYED! However, had the toss happened, what would the skipper do? Bowl first? Overcast conditions, green wicket, maybe yes but bowling first is always a risk, if there is nothing on offer for the bowlers, it could well cost you the game. It did cost Bangladesh the game when they elected to bowl against the Kiwis in the second Test in similar conditions.

We might just see a few changes from both the sides! Especially from England, Sam Billings for sure will be making his debut in place of Buttler. Ollie Pope might also come in for Jonny Bairstow who has a hand injury. For the Aussies, there is a sure change as they will be getting in Head for Marcus Harris and move Usman Khawaja up the order! Rightly so, it is difficult to drop someone who scored two tons in the same game.

Coming to the hosts now! For the very first time in this series they were made to work hard! They have had everything their way and it has actually been easy going for them. One believes though, if rain had not played a part in the last game, it could have well been 4-0. They though would want to end this with a win.

Before we start talking about Australia, the news is not the best to begin with. It is drizzling at the moment. There is still a long time to go for the game to begin and the forecast ain't that bad so fingers crossed.

How good must England be feeling after that draw! That look on Ben Stokes' face in the last over said it all. He was dearly hoping they just did not lose again. The visitors have had a poor tour, they have been beaten black and blue by the Aussies and have been no competition before the last game. It will be a huge sigh of relief if they can end this with a win.

The 4th Test was a hard fought draw which not only ended the hopes of a whitewash but would have surely boosted the confidence of the England side. They have endured an extremely poor tour so far but a win here will do wonders. Can they beat the odds and end the tour on a high? Well, they will yet again have to play out of their skins. This is another pink-ball Test and we all know how good the Aussies are in the Day/Night game. Also, after last game’s frustration they will be eager to end the series with a win. Let’s hope we have yet another thriller. Welcome to the coverage.
... DAY 1, SESSION 1 ...

We are back for the third innings! The English players stride out to the middle and they are followed by David Warner and Usman Khawaja who will open the batting for Australia. Stuart Broad will start with the ball. Here we go...
... Third Innings ...

Well, the Aussie pacers had their tail up today. Pat Cummins showed why he is the best of the best as he ended up with 4 wickets and it wasn't just the wickets but just how well he bowled throughout the innings. Scott Boland was just relentless with his around the off stump probing line and Mitchell Starc did what he does best and cleaned up the tail in a jiffy. Green too bowled well and picked up a wicket whereas Nathan Lyon wasn't even required. A dominating display from the bowlers and now, can the Aussie openers stick around and pile on the pressure? We'll find out in about 10 minutes of time.

As many as 14 wickets have already fallen on Day 2 and we might see a couple more. Three out of the top four English batters got starts but none of them were able to play a big innings, not even a half-century from anyone. Stokes and Pope too failed and it was the debutant, Sam Billings who looked most comfortable out there in the middle and seemed to be timing the ball well. Chris Woakes hung around with him and the pair got some quick runs after the break. Billings though fell but Woakes and Wood did manage some streaky boundaries. The last three wickets fell in the space of nine deliveries and this has left the visitors with a hefty deficit.

What a brilliant allround display with the ball from the Aussie quicks. They have managed to bundle out the visitors for under 200 yet again and have a big first innings lead of 115 runs as well. England, well they were already reeling at 124 for 6 at the Tea break but the tailenders have at least managed to cut short the Aussie lead, which otherwise would have been absolutely mammoth. Their bowlers now have a chance to bowl under lights and look for early breakthroughs. The bis question is that will Ollie Robinson bowl tonight or not?

OUT! BOWLED! Pat Cummins has the last laugh and gets his fourth wicket of the innings.He serves a length ball, around off. Wood hangs back and looks to slog but misses it completely. The ball cannons onto his off stump and England are bundled out for 188!
Commentary.Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: In the air...but safe! This is a length ball, around off. Wood looks to heave it away but it goes off the outer half of the blade and falls just in front of the cover fielder who runs back to grab it. The batters take a couple.
SIX! Whooaa, where did that come from? Full ball, in the slot, around middle. Wood hangs back and sends it sailing way over the long on fence for a maximum.
Full ball, around off. Wood backs away and drills it towards mid off.
Ollie Robinson is the last man in for England.
OUT! CHOPPED ON! This is a very full ball, outside off. Broad looks to dig it out without any feet movement. Broad gets a thick inside edge onto his off stump. England lose their ninth wicket.
Commentary.Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Whooaa! That missed the off stump by an inch! A low full toss, just outside off. Broad hops in his crease and then looks to block it but he misses.
Fuller in length, outside off. Stuart Broad squeezes it out watchfully.
Broad backs away so starc follows him and bowls a yorker, around leg. Stuart Broad fails to dig it out.
Stuart Broad is in at number 10.

Mitchell Starc says he's heard two noises and Pat Cummins does go for the review. Indeed there were two noises as the third umpire confirms on Hotspot that there's a slight tickle off the bat. The keeper wasn't sure but kudos to the skipper for believing in his bowler and the fact the Australia have missed out on two reviews earlier on might have also played a part in this review. Chris Woakes though has to walk back.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! JEEZ! What a review from the Aussies! This was a good-length ball, around leg. Woakes looks to flick but he only manages a tickle, which ricochets off his hips and then goes to the keeper. Alex Carey, behind the sticks makes no mistake and Starc appeals. The umpire says no and Pat Cummins opts for a review. The UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball was passing the bat and Chris Woakes is a goner.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Good effort from Nathan Lyon in the deep! Length ball, around off. Woakes backs away and drives it past the cover fielder. Lyon runs across to his right and dives just in front of the ropes to save a couple of runs for his side.
On a length, just outside off. Wood lunges forward and pushes it towards the mid off fielder.
Cummins bangs it into the deck, around middle. Wood looks to pull but he misses.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mark Wood looks to drive but the ball zips past his blade.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! A length ball, outside off. Mark Wood prods and smacks it through the vacant cover region for a boundary.
In the air...but it lands safely! Full ball, around leg. Chris Woakes chips it uppishly to wide of the deep mid-wicket fielder for a run.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Wood looks to drive on the up but it goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Good-looking shot. Pitched up, on off, looking to bring it back in. Wood punches it nicely through mid off. The fielder though chases it down and saves a run for his team.
Back of a length, over middle. Woakes hops back and keeps it down towards deep square leg for another one.
A length ball, around leg and at 146 kph. Wood looks to tuck it away off his hips but misses and the ball goes off the thigh pads towards deep square leg for one.
Length, on middle. Woakes works it away nicely through mid-wicket and picks up a single.
FOUR! Chris Woakes is profiting in the third man region. Fuller, on middle and pushed across the batter. Woakes edges it past gully and picks up yet another boundary.
Good running. Around middle and leg, Wood dabs it towards mid-wicket and scampers through for one.
Mitchell Starc (8-1-41-1) is back on.
Flashy shot but no connection. Full, around off. Woakes backs away and swings hard at it but misses it completely.
On a good length, on middle. Chris Woakes makes a bit of room and looks to heave it to the leg side but misses and gets hit in the mid riff.
On off, Wood stands tall and pushes it through covers for a run.
LEG BYE! Short of a length, at the body. Woakes gets it off the thigh pads on the leg side and gets a leg bye.
And again. This time it's even closer to the off pole and Woakes gets beaten past the outside edge.
Cummins is right on the money. Good-length ball, around off and this is angled in. The ball straightens after pitching and Woakes gets squared all ends up.
Pat Cummins (11-2-32-3) brings himself into the attack.
Sliding down leg. A fuller delivery, attacking the pads. Wood looks to flick but gets cramped for room and gets struck on the pads.
A bit width on offer and this is eased towards deep point for one.

FOUR BYES! A bit wayward from Scott Boland. It's the inswinger but the ball starts on leg stump and just keeps going further down. Carey dives to his left but can't get to it. The ball races away into the fine leg fence.
Length again, outside off. Woakes has a swing at it but misses.

FOUR! Another edgy boundary but England will take those at this stage. Length again, outside off. Woakes pushes at it and gets it in between third slip and gully as the ball races towards the third man fence.
Play and a miss. To be honest, I don't know how anyone would play that one. Beautifully angled in from around off and the ball just shapes away so perfectly, leaving the batter bamboozled.
A length ball, angled into middle. Wood jams it out towards gully and looks for the single but the fielder does well to make the stop.
Mark Wood walks out to bat now.

OUT! TAKEN! The plan has worked for Australia and they get Sam Billings. A well-directed short ball from Cameron Green, right around the helmet. Billings cannot get out of the way and goes for the pull shot. He is a bit late and the ball goes off the top edge and flies towards the fine leg fence. Scott Boland takes an easy catch and this opens the floodgates for Australia to wrap things up here.
Commentary.Howout: c Scott Boland b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: On off. Solidly blocked out by Billings.
A good-length ball, angled into middle and leg. Woakes tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Pitched up, on off and punched back towards the bowler. The big man does well to get low to his left and make a stop.

SIX! All the way! Woakes thought he was gone for all money but gets just about enough on it. Banged in short, over middle. Woakes has both feet in the air as he hooks it away. The ball carries over the man at the square leg fence for a maximum.
FOUR! Edgy boundary! Slightly fuller and outside off, inviting the drive. Billings pushes at it with soft hands and gets an outside edge which runs away to the backward point fence.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, at the body. Woakes looks to tuck it away leg side but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads onto the leg side and they get a leg bye.
FOUR! Boland just overpitches and Woakes with a lovely cover drive. Fullish ball, around off and Woakes gets forward to stroke it through the cover region for a boundary.
Around the top of off and blocked out.
Shorter in length, over middle. Woakes looks to keep it down off the back foot but the ball goes off the inside edge towards backward square leg. They come back for a couple.

This is just unreal bowling from Boland! A length ball, angled into off and the ball just shapes away ever so beautifully. Woakes is caught on the crease and has a poke at it but gets beaten all ends up yet again.
FOUR! Classy from the debutant! Green serves a half-volley, outside off. Sam Billings lunges forward and carves it past the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Sam Billings is solid in his defense this time around.
JAFFA! Back of a length, just outside off and jagging back in late. Billings stays back to block but the ball sneaks through his bat through to the keeper.
On a length, around middle. Sam Billings presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Short of a length, around off. Sam Billings gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it out.
This was a length ball, way outside off. Sam Billings leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, around off. Woakes defends it to the off side. End of another probing over from Boland!

BEATEN ALL ENDS UP! Another peach of a delivery from Boland! A length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Woakes gets stuck in his crease as he tries to push it through the off side. The ball zips past his outside edge.
This is a length ball, around off, cramping Woakes for room. He does well to tap it towards cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes leaves it alone watchfully.
