On off and angling back in sharply. Smith keeps it out on the leg side.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. This is worked through square leg for a single by Boland.
Fuller in length, angled at the pads. Boland looks to flick but the ball skids through and gets hit on the pads.
Length again, around middle and Boland keeps it out.

Ooh! Sam Billings has the ball up in the air and looks like he's certain. The ball is pitched up and is angled into off stump. The ball straightens after pitching and whizzes past the outside edge of Boland's bat. Joe Root has a think about it but decides against it. The replay shows that the ball missed the bat.
Slightly pitched up, outside off and just moving away off the seam. Boland makes an easy leave.
Banged in short but spilled down the leg side. Steven Smith isn't interested in playing that one.
Around the top of off and this is edged down through backward point for a run.

Uppish but safe! Wood hits the length hard at 143 kph and bowls it on off stump. Scott Boland is pushed on the back foot as he tries to fend it away. The ball comes off the handle of the bat but falls safely around silly mid off.
Well bowled. A length ball, angled in from outside off but this one shapes away after pitching and zips past the outside edge.
Back of a length, around the hips. Steven Smith shuffles across and works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
On a good length, on off and angled in. Smith hops back to defend.
A length ball, on middle and angling in. Boland looks to keep it out but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Sliding down leg this one.
With that wicket of David Warner, Stuart Broad becomes England's leading wicket-taker in the Ashes with 129 wickets. He moves ahead of Sir Ian Botham who has 128 Ashes wickets to his name.
Full, on middle. Boland manages to block it out.
Shortish ball, outside off and shaping away. Boland doesn't play at it.
Just a bit too high yet again. On a length, around off and this one just nips back in off the surface. Boland gets caught on the crease and gets pinged on the pads as well.
Slightly fuller this time, on off. Boland gets his bat right behind the line of the ball to block.
Robinson hits the length hard and bowls it outside off. Boland taps it back onto the deck.
Boland is off the mark. Around the top of off, edged down with soft hands through backward point and they get one. Scott Boland will retain strike.
A length ball, around off and kept out on the off side by Boland.
Back of a length, on off. Boland hops to defend and that is probably a much easier length to defend for a nightwatchman.
Ooh, that one just whizzed past the helmet. Another short ball, around off and at 142 kph. Boland ducks down to get away from it but almost get nailed on the head.
This is a fiery spell from Wood. A length ball, around 146 kph and on off. Boland does well to get a ball on it.
Who will come out to bat now? Will the Aussies send in a night watchman? Yes, they do. Out comes Scott Boland.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That is a brute of a delivery from Mark Wood. Wood bends his back and angles in a pacy short delivery at 147.7 kph. The ball is directed right at the helmet and given the sting on the ball, Usman Khawaja had almost no chance of getting out of the way. Khawaja did try but just couldn't keep his bat down. The ball just comes off the gloves and Sam Billings takes a sharp catch to his right. England are looking for more wickets here.
Commentary.Howout: c Sam Billings b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: On middle. Blocked out.
Robinson is bowling a good length but given his height, the ball's always going over the stumps. Good-length ball, angled into leg stump and Smith gets hit on the pads yet again.
It's not easy out there at the moment. A lot of inside edges and balls hitting the pads. A length ball, on off and angling in. Smith looks to push at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
This one is sliding on the pads, Smith looks to leave but gets rapped on the pads.
Back of a length, nipping back in from around off. Smith gets caught on the crease and gets hit high on the pads.
Good-length ball, over the leg stump. Smith shuffles across yet again and looks to flick but misses.
Length again, angled into off. Khawaja defends it solidly off the front foot.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Khawaja manages to keep it out.
Back of a length, on off. Khawaja hops to keep it down.
FOUR! Mark Wood has had absolutely no luck in this series. Around the top of off and the outside edge is found yet again. The ball keeps low off the bat and runs down into the third man fence.

Was there an edge? Was it LBW? Peach of a delivery from Wood. A length ball, angled into off and middle. The ball just seams away after pitching. Khawaja gets squared up and the ball just clips the back leg and goes to the keeper. Huge shouts from the visitors but nothing given. The replay shows that it did hit the pads and was just a bit high.
Wood comes 'round the wicket and starts off with a gentle half-volley, on the pads. Khawaja clips it towards deep square leg and picks up a couple.
A change from both ends now as Mark Wood comes on to bowl.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head! Fuller in length, outside off. Smith prods but does not offer any shot to this one. The ball hits him low on his pad.
Good-length ball, around off. Steven Smith blocks it out.

FOUR! A bit streaky from Smith and he is lucky that the ball did not go straight to the leg slip fielder. Back of a length, around middle and leg. Smith looks to shoulder his arms to it but the ball just brushes his gloves and goes in between the diving keeper and the leg slip fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Steven Smith stays back to defend.
A bit fuller this time, outside off. Smith does not offer any shot to this one.
Robinson starts with a length ball, around off. Smith shuffles across and blocks it out towards point.
Here comes the first bowling change. Ollie Robinson is finally fit enough to bowl.
Fuller in length, outside off. Usman Khawaja lets it through to the keeper.
Another ball, on a length, around middle. Usman Khawaja gets behind the line of the ball to defend.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Usman Khawaja blocks it out solidly.
Length ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! Full ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja looks for a booming drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Usman Khawaja looks to block but he misses and gets hit near his thigh pad.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Usman Khawaja stays back and pulls it along the ground towards fine leg. He finally gets off the mark and gets a loud cheer from the crowd!
AND AGAIN! Length ball, around off and curling away late. Usman Khawaja looks to defend but the ball whistles past his blade.
BEATEN! Back of a length, around middle and going on with the angle. Usman Khawaja looks to block but he misses.
Woakes drags his length back, outside off. Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms to this one.
Fuller this time, oustdie off. Usman Khawaja pushes it towards mid off.
On a length, just outside off and angling across the batter. Usman Khawaja looks to defend but the ball goes past his blade.
Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Smith presses forward to block and yells 'NO RUN'.
BEATEN! Top delivery from Broad! Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Smith has a poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Fuller in length, well outside off. Steven Smith prods but does not offer any shot to this one.
Back of a length, outside off and nipping back in late. Smith leaves it alone watchfully.
Leg bye! Short of a length, jagging back in late from outside off. Usman Khawaja misses his tuck on the leg side and gets hit near his thigh pad. The batters sneak in a leg bye.
Good-length ball, nipping back in down leg. Usman Khawaja misses his flick this time.
On a length, around off. Steven Smith defends it out.
FOUR! No need to run for these kind of shots! Fuller in length, outside off. Smith lunges forward and caresses it through the vacant region for a boundary.
A slight mix-up but no harm done! Good-length ball, just outside off. Steven Smith stands tall and taps it to the off side. He takes off for a run but it sent back by Khawaja.
Short of a length, around off. Steven Smith hangs back and blocks it to the off side.
Length ball, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
FOUR! An appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Good-length ball, angling in from off. Smith looks to flick but he gets an inside edge onto his pads and it races away to the fine leg fence.
This one was on a length, well outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Short of a length, jagging back in down leg. Khawaja misses his flick as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around off. Usman Khawaja prods and blocks it out.
Broad comes 'round the wicket and serves a length delivery, outside off. Usman Khawaja makes an assured leave.
On a length, nipping back in from off. Steven Smith glances it towards fine leg for a run.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Steven Smith looks to leave it but the ball hits him high on his body.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Usman Khawaja lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, on middle. Usman Khawaja defends it towards mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.

Right on the buzzer, Joe Root does go for the review. There was a huge noise and in real-time it looked really close, even the on-air commentators felt the review should be taken. There's nothing on Hotspot and UltraEdge confirms the same. The ball just clipped the pad on its way. A brilliant decision from the onfield umpire Paul Wilson and Khawaja survives.

NOT OUT! Usman Khawaja ESCAPES! Top delivery nonetheless from Woakes! This was on a length, around middle and shaping away a bit. Khawaja stays back to block but he misses and the ball just clips his pad before going to the keeper. Joe Root opts for a review very late but the Ball Tracker indicates that there was no bat involved and England lose a review.
Back of a length, just outside off. Usman Khawaja does not offer any shot to this one.
Length delivery, around off. Usman Khawaja presses forward and keeps it out watchfully.
Wow, that one just kept on going down leg. A cross-seamer probably from Broad, on a length and angled down leg. The ball goes further down leg and Smith makes a stylish leave.
A length ball, swinging down the leg side. Left alone by Smith.
Broad goes full and looks to skid one through bat and pad. Smith goes back and forth to keep it out. Lovely footwork from Smith though.
Good take. Broad spills this one well down the leg side and Billings does well to dive to his left and pouch that one.
Slightly fuller, sliding onto the pads. Smith punches it towards mid on.
This is angled into middle. Smith goes across his crease and works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
A length ball, close to the off stump and Khawaja makes a good leave.
Fullish ball, on off and shaping in. Khawaja blocks it out.
Smith is off the mark and he will be mightily relieved. Good-length ball, outside off and shaping away. This one bounces a bit extra but Smith is able to work it through covers for a single.
Around the top of middle and blocked out by Smith.
Smith is on a pair and just about manages to fend this one away. A length ball, attacking middle and leg. Smith keeps it out.
Steven Smith is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The dangerman, Marnus Labuschagne is sent packing early. A length ball, around middle and angling down the leg side. Labuschagne shuffles across his stumps a bit and just like the first innings, that's his undoing. Labuschagne looks to flick it fine but gets a slight tickle on it and Sam Billings springs to his left to take a great catch. That's his first catch in Test cricket and boy, the whole team is pumped up for him. Root shakes his hand and maybe, just maybe England have an opportunity here.
Commentary.Howout: c Sam Billings b Chris Woakes

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball, outside off and left alone.
An action replay of the previous delivery as this one shapes away from outside off. Khawaja doesn't play at it.
Slightly fuller and wider, left alone by Khawaja.
Close! A length ball, hurled across from 'round the wicket and angled into off stump. Khawaja makes an assured leave.

Misfield and Broad vents his frustration. Around that fourth stump line and once again Labuschagne is drawn forward a bit. He plays it with soft hands towards point, where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
On middle. Blocked out.

Oh, careful there Rory Burns. Back of a length, on off. Labuschagne squeezes it through the gully region and Burns chases it down. Just as Burns slides, he gets his foot stuck in the turf. Three taken.
Peach! Woakes goes slightly fuller, around off. The batter is drawn forward and hye gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball shapes away beautifully.
Woakes goes full and bowls it on off. Labuschagne jams it out.
That one nipped back in sharply. A length ball, around off and ends up around middle and leg. Labuschagne looks to block but gets hit on the body.
Woakes hits the length hard, around off and Labuschagne keeps it down on the off side.
On a good length, in that channel around off. Labuschagne goes back and forth to block and gets beaten by the away movement.
Chris Woakes to bowl from the other end.
Broad switches to 'round the wicket and delivers a fullish ball, outside off. This one shapes away late but Khawaja make an easy leave.
Australia are off the mark. Length again, angled at the pads. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a single.
Well, that swung a long way. Angled in from outside off and the ball ends up going way down the leg side. Sam Billings does really well to jump to his left and pouch it.
Marnus Labuschagne walks in at number 3.

OUT! TAKEN! Stuart Broad has done it again! He proves to be David Warner's nemesis yet again as Warner walks back on a pair. Length again, this time there's some width on offer. Warner is stuck on the crease and instead of thrashing at it, he looks to work it past backward point. The ball though goes uppishly to the right of point and Ollie Pope flies to his right to grab a stunner. Just the start the visitors were looking for. Can they build on it?
Commentary.Howout: c Ollie Pope b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: This is angled into middle and leg, Warner watchfully defends it out.
Lovely start from Stuart Broad. A length ball, outside off and this one just zips away from David Warner as he looks to block it.

Cummins gets back on the stage and lifts the silverware! His team joins him and they pose for the cameras! That ends the Ashes and we thank you for joining us for the coverage. Hope you enjoyed it as much as we enjoyed covering these games for you. Do keep us company for we have plenty of cricket coming up. The U-19 World Cup, the BBL, India's ODI series against South Africa - you name it. We look forward to your company for all this and more. Take care and goodbye for now!

Travis Head is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH AND PLAYER OF THE SERIES! Travis Head says that he is happy to have an impact and says that his century in this Test match is a bit special because the conditions were just a bit more challenging. He adds that he has worked a lot on his game in the past couple of years and there were always batters ahead of him so he had to put on a good show. Mentions that all the players in the team are performing really well and says that there's competition for every single place in the side. He ends by saying that these are challenging times and thanks the English team for coming out here to play,

Pat Cummins, the winning Australian captain, says that this is what dreams are made off and to win the series 4-0 is a great feeling. Adds that he is really happy as captain with the bowling but jokes that Lyon may not agree with his decisions in this Test. Praises Green for how he has played throughout the series with both the bat and the ball. Also praises Boland for the way he has bowled. Mentions that he is excited about their series overseas as it would provide different challenges. To finish things off, he thanks the ECB, CA and the English players for touring under tough global conditions, and also the general public for their support.

Joe Root, the English skipper, says that it has been a frustrating and tough tour and they just haven't been able to put on consistent performances throughout a match. He adds that this is a challenge they faced and they need to go home and reflect on this and it won't be long before they play Test cricket again. Mentions that they were completed outplayed in all departments of the game and acknowledges that their opponents were superior. He then gives credit to his bowlers as well and hails Mark Wood for his sensational work throughout the series. He ends by congratulating the Australian skipper and his team for the series win.
Right then. Plenty of interviews coming up in the presentation. Stick around.

England had to chase down 271 runs to win this game. It looked unlikely given how they have batted so far but the opening pair of Zak Crawley and Rory Burns did a really good job in the second session of Day 3. They put on 68 runs together but the wicket of Burns just before Tea was all that Australia needed to make inroads in the English batting. A disappointing finish for England. They played well in patches but lacked the killer instinct to finish things off. Mark Wood was probably their standout player. Never gave up, never got tired, always gave it his all. Take a bow, lad!

England though did not give up and had a brilliant outing with the ball in the second innings. Mark Wood led from the front with a career-best 6-wicket haul and Stuart Broad took 3. The Australian batters had a tough time as Mark Wood attacked them with plenty of short ones. Still, the contributions by Cameron Green and Alex Carey lower down in the order got them to 155 with a total lead of 270.

England had a really tough first innings with the bat. Their top order faltered once again and it was some handy batting from the lower order that somehow got them to 188. The Aussies did not need Nathan Lyon to bowl as the pacers did the job with ease. Pat Cummins led the attack with 4 wickets and was well supported by Mitchell Starc's 3 wickets.

Earlier in the Test, England started really well on Day 1 with 3 early wickets but the Aussies recovered well. Led by a brilliant ton by Travis Head and a fifty by Cameron Green, they went onto score 303 runs in the first innings. The English bowlers bowled decently with everyone with the exception of Joe Root taking wickets.

But the bowling of Cameron Green changed things completely. He got the wicket of Rory Burns right at the stroke of Tea and then after the break, he took 2 more to put them in big trouble. The stand between Joe Root and Ben Stokes was probably the last hope for England and once that was broken, they had no answers to some brilliant and consistent bowling from the Aussies. The pacers ruled the roost as Nathan Lyon did not get to bowl a single over in the game. England lost 10 wickets for just 56 runs and that tells you the entire story.

The target for England was quite big but they had plenty of time to chase it down. It was quite certain that there would be a result in the game given how much time there was. But for a change, the English openers put on a brilliant stand at the top. They batted with intent and got boundaries when the bowlers erred. Things were looking great for them in the second session and it looked like they could potentially win this game.

IT IS 4-0! What a show by Australia! They have dominated the entire series and this game was no different. When the English bowlers put them under pressure, they punched back. Their pacers had the batters on the feet through the series and were relentless. England had a very tough tour. After being outplayed in the first three Tests, they put on a great fight in Sydney to draw the game. They played really well in this Test too and had a really good chance to win this game. But they lost their plot in one session. Yes, in one session. The wheels came off the rails in the post-Tea session here and they crumbled under pressure. Take nothing away from the Aussies though as they will keep the Ashes Urn and there will be a party for sure!

OUT! BOWLED! What a way to end the series as it is the captain, Pat Cummins, who gets the final wicket and takes his team to victory! Full, fast and dead straight. Ollie Robinson moves across the leg stump and just has no answer for the yorker. The ball shatters the stumps and AUSTRALIA WIN BY 146 RUNS AND WIN THE ASHES 4-0!
Commentary.Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Another short ball, on middle. Broad backs away and plays it towards backward point for a run.
Stuart Broad is the last batter for England in the Ashes.

OUT! BOWLED! Cummins gets his man! Mark Wood knows there's no point in hanging around and looks to go out with a few lusty blows. A short ball, outside off and Wood shuffles across looking to hook it away. The ball hurries onto him and he ends up getting an inside edge back onto the stumps and that's just been the story of this series. The English team just throwing in the towel way too early.
Commentary.Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Up and over! Length ball, on off. Wood heaves it over mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Wood will go down swinging! Full, outside off. He clears his front leg and slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Ollie Robinson is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Edged and taken wonderfully by Alex Carey! Boland goes fuller, around off. Chris Woakes gives himself room and goes for the big heave on the leg side. The ball comes off the outside edge and flies to the right of the keeper. Alex Carey springs and takes a gem of a catch. Woakes perishes and Australia just two wickets away now from victory.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter in length, around off and angled in. Woakes looks to hook but doesn't get any bat on it.
Back of a length, Woakes opens the face of the bat and guides it towards gully.
FOUR! Nicely played. On middle and leg, Woakes flicks it in front of square on the leg side and picks up a boundary.
Around off. Blocked.
On off, pushed towards covers for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Wood hops and works it on the off side for one.
A quick bumper, outside off. Wood has a swipe at it but misses it completely.
Ooh, a nasty bouncer but Woakes does well. Shorter in length, angled towards the helmet. Woakes somehow manages to get it behind square for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Wood taps it through covers for a single.
Mark Wood is the new man in.

OUT! Cleaned up! The last of the recognized batters perishes and Australia all over the visitors right now. Pat Cummins hurls across a length ball that is angled into leg stump. Ollie Pope walks right across his stumps as he looks to flick it away. He misses and pays the ultimate price as the ball crashes into leg stump. Just three wickets to go now and England cannot believe it.
Commentary.Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Around off. Pope tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
A length ball, angling into middle. Woakes manages to defend it out.
Back of a length, around off. Woakes takes it eye off the ball and just about manages to get a bat on it.
On off. Blocked out.
Full again, trying to attack the pads. Woakes drives it towards mid off.
Fuller in length, on off. This is pushed towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Soft dismissal for Sam Billings and England are just crumbling under pressure. A length ball, angling into middle and leg. There is a bit of an extra bounce on offer for Scott Boland and that is what catches Billings out. He doesn't move his feet and is caught on the crease as he flicks it uppishly and straight into the hands of the skipper, Pat Cummins at mid on. It's all but over now for the visitors. Chris Woakes is the new man in.
Commentary.Howout: c Pat Cummins b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Blocked out.
Length and on the pads. Billings gets it off his pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
Short and on off. Pope pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed towards gully.
Full and on off. Billings gets the outside edge but it rolls towards the slip cordon.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked out.
Fuller, around off. Pope works it past square leg for a couple.
Really good spirit by Root. While he was going back to the hut, a bunch of kids came and stood near the steps. Root gave them his gloves in what was a great gesture.
Length ball, outside off. Pope gets forward to block it.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full, on the pads. Billings looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball goes to the leg side and they sneak in a leg bye.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, on off. This comes back in. Billings looks to block but gets hit high on the pads.
In the last 10 overs, 17 runs have been scored for 2 wickets. Relentless bowling from the Aussies and they are right back on top.
Length ball, around off. Pushed towards gully but Green dives to stop the ball. A big cheer from the crowd.
Ouch! Short and on off. Pope looks to sway away but does not get low enough. The ball hits his shoulder.
On a length, on off. Pope blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, outside off. Pope goes back to block but it zips past the outside edge.
On lengh, outside off. Pushed to cover.
Angled into middle. Billings defends it solidly off the front foot.
Good-length ball, wide of off stump. Billings has a poke at it and edges it down towards gully.
Sam Billings is in with his team in deep, deep trouble.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, boy. Speechless. Simply speechless. Root has a wry smile on his face and to be honest, there is nothing else he can do. Boland though is over the moon and he can do no wrong in the series. That is a really unfortunate way to get out. Lands on a length, on off and simply does not rise up! It shoots low and goes under the bat as Root is in the crease to block it. It goes onto hit the off pole and Root walks back. Things could get over soon now.
Commentary.Howout: b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Root goes for the punch but misses.

DRINKS! Joe Root has an issue with his bat as it has cracked a bit and calls for a change. The umpires take this opportunity to call for a Drinks break. It has certainly been enthralling action in this final session so far and England are just about hanging on in this match. A wicket or two in the next 15 mins or so and the hosts will be licking their lips. Joe Root holds the key here for the visitors but does need support from the other end as well.
On a length, lands on off and stays a bit low. Root gets his bat down in time to block. Looks like it hit him low on the bat and he needs to change it.
Boland serves a length ball, just outside off. Root takes a step down the track and blocks it.
Scott Boland (8-3-11-0) is back into the attack.
Beaten again! Cummins bowls it full and just outside off. Pope looks to block it from the crease and the ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short, on off. Pope sits under it.
Length ball, outside off. Pope goes at it with his hands and blocks it.
Short of a length, around off. Root pushes it past gully to get a single.
Length ball, around off. Driven down the ground for a single. 100 up for England with that single.
Length ball, around off. Root dabs it towards gully and Green moves to his right and stops it. He can do no wrong here!
Short and down the leg side. Pulled down to fine leg for a couple.

Short and on the body. Root drops his hands expecting that the ball will go past his shoulder. But it stays a bit low and hits the bottom of the bat. Luckily for him, the ball rolls to the slip cordon.
Length, on off. Blocked out.

FOUR! Misfield and a boundary! Length and on off. Root drives it nicely and the man at mid off misfields after diving to his right. The ball tickles to the fence. That brings up 5000 runs as Test captain for Joe Root.
Very full again, around off. Root pushes it to cover.
Nice and full, on off. Pope stays on the front to block it.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Pope ducks under it.
Fuller and a bit wider. Left alone.
Beaten! Perfect delivery. Length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Pope looks to block that from the crease but it holds its line and goes past the outside edge.
On a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Pope leaves it alone.
Bumper, down the leg side. Pope sits under it.
Fuller, around off. Pushed past cover for one.
Ollie Pope is the new man in.

OUT! TAKEN! GONE! England in big, big trouble now! A brilliant catch by Lyon and Starc is pumped! He gets the important wicket of Stokes at the right moment for Australia. A surprise bumper, on middle. Stokes goes for the pull but gets the top edge. The ball goes towards deep square leg. Lyon, who hasn't had a lot to do in this game, runs in from the fence. He dives forward and takes a very good catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: The crowd is really getting into it now. Starc is being cheered in his run up.
A touch shorter and touch wider. Root slaps it towards deep point for one.
Length ball, lands on off and angles away. Root blocks it towards cover.
Nice and full, around off. Root stays in the crease to block it.
Full and on the pads.Stokes flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
Play and a miss! Short of a length, outside off. Root goes for the cut shot but misses.
On a length, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Full, on off. Root blocks it from the crease.
Oh jaffa! Length ball, lands on the off pole. Root has to play and looks to block. The ball nips away a bit and goes past the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Root hops back and pushes it to cover.
Pat Cummins (6-0-26-0) brings himself back on. He replaces Green.
Full and down the leg side. Stokes misses the flick.
Oh boy. 72-28 Australia is what the broadcaster's win predictor says now.
Nice and full, on off. Stokes blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Stokes pushes it nicely to mid off again.
A lovely push to mid off for nothing.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes blocks it from the crease.
Fired full, on the pads. Stokes flicks it past mid on for a couple.
Length ball, on off and this is pushed towards covers for a run.
Ouch! This is angled at the body from 'round the wicket. Stokes looks to pull but is through his shot early and gets a blow around the ribs.
On off. Blocked out.
Good-length ball, on off. This is squeezed to the right of point for a quick single.
Length this time, around off. Root taps it on the off side.
Green certainly is on song here. A well-directed bumper, on off. Joe Root does well to get his head out of the way in time.
A sort of half-volley, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes flicks it nicely but straight to the fielder at wide mid on.
Shorter in length and well outside off. Stokes isn't going to play at that one.
Beaten! Nicely angled in, around off and the ball just holds its line after pitching. Stokes looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Starc drifts onto the pads and Root tickles it towards fine leg for a single.
Length again, around off and pushing Root back to defend.
A length ball, on off. Root hops on the back foot to defend.
Change. Mitchell Starc (4-0-18-0) is brought back on now.
Probably the most important pair for England in the middle now. They need a big stand between these two. Australia are aware of that and would want to separate these two as soon as they can.
Good-length again, on off and angling in. Root gets it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg for one and opens his account.
Green is making the ball talk here. On a good length, around off and this one nips back in sharply off the surface. Root gets caught on the crease and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Around off, kept out by Root.
Back of a length, outside off. Stokes hangs back and steers it through backward point for a single.
Ben Stokes is the new man in. England have two new batters out in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cameron Green is turning this match on its head all by himself! Green pitches this one up, around off and this one seems to be going on with the angle but just straightens a bit, enough to get the knick. Zak Crawley is drawn forward and he plays for the line but is undone by the late movement. The ball goes off the outside edge and Alex Carey dives to his right to take a sharp catch. Crawley was looking so good out there and now the visitors are certainly under pressure with two new batters out in the middle.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Around the top of middle. Crawley keeps it out on the off side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Root is outside the crease and is outside the off pole as well. He leaves it alone.

LEG BYE! Apart from Joe Root no one knew where that ball went. Length again, outside off. Zak Crawley shuffles across the stumps and looks to whip it leg side. He misses and the ball goes off his pads towards backward point. They do eventually get a leg bye.
Boland hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Crawley hops back to defend.
Lovely away movement again from Boland. Pitched up, a bit wide of the off stump and shaping in. Crawley leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off and dabbed down towards short cover.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Crawley keeps it out.
Right on the money from Green. Root defends it nicely off the front foot.
Joe Root makes his way out to the middle. England need 189 to win and they need a big partnership here. Two slips and a gully in place.

OUT! Chopped on! Cameron Green does get the wicket of Dawid Malan and he is elated. Malan was troubled by the short ball and that extra zip that Green is getting off the surface. This is on a good length, close to off stump and just nips back in ever so slightly. Dawid Malan is indecisive and has a late poke at it. His feet don't move and the inside edge is found. The ball goes back onto hit the off stump. Is this the opening the hosts were looking for?
Commentary.Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: A good bumper again, around the off pole. Malan sways away from it.
On top of off and Malan stays solid in defense.
Green is certainly getting the better of Malan out there. On a good length, around off and angling in sharply. Malan gets cut in half and has no answer to that one.
Green is getting a good zip through the surface. Short of a good length, outside off and shaping away a bit. Malan throws his hands at it but misses.
Good-length ball, on off and defended out.
A bit uppish, but through the gap. Length again, around off and driven on the up towards sweeper cover for a single.
Nicely bowled, in that channel around the off stump. Malan shoulders arms.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan hangs back and taps it towards point.
Boland goes full and angles it on off stump. Malan pushes it out towards mid off.
Around the top of off, Malan blocks it out.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Length again, outside off. Zak Crawley stands tall and creams it through the covers for a boundary.
Lucky! On a length, around off. Malan looks for the booming cover drive but gets an inside edge past the stumps. The batters get a single as well.
Short and wide, Malan leaves it alone.
Shorter in length again, outside off. Malan makes the leave.

The physio is out in the middle. Malan has been hit on the helmet so as per the concussion protocol, the physio is out to have a look at him. A change of helmet and Malan seems fine now. The new helmet still has the price tag on it!

Ouch! What a ripper! Green angles in a quick short ball, around the helmet. Dawid Malan just takes his eyes off the ball a bit and gets stung on the grill of the helmet. That one must have shaken up the batter. Luckily it didn't go through the gap inside the grill. Hope he is okay.
FOUR! Positive intent from Dawid Malan. A length ball, wide of off stump. Malan stands tall and slaps it past the diving fielder at point for a boundary.
That one moved late. Slightly pitched up, outside off and Crawley makes an assured leave. Maiden over from Scott Boland.
On off. Defended towards mid off.
On a length, around the fifth-stump line. Crawley defends it solidly off the front foot.
Length again, around middle. Crawley keeps it out towards mid-wicket.
A lovely shot for no run. Pitched up, on middle and the straight drive comes out. Crawley hits it dead straight and hits the stumps on the opposite end.
On a good length, over off. Crawley stays solid in defense.
Scott Boland to bowl from the other end.

FOUR! Streaky boundary to get off the mark from Dawid Malan but he will take it. Full and outside off, Malan throws his hands at it and manages to squeeze it behind point for a boundary. Under 200 required now to win.
Green bends his back this time and angles in a short ball, at the body. Malan does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
Green pulls back his length a bit and angles it at the body. Malan looks to block but gets caught on the crease and the ball hits him on the arms.
Green goes full and on off. Malan pushes it out towards mid off.
Length ball, right around the top of off. Malan taps it towards covers.
We are back for the final session here on Day 3. Zak Crawley is joined by Dawid Malan, who will be on strike. Cameron Green is ready to steam in and complete his unfinished over.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

Well then, from the looks of the session that has gone by, Australia seemed to have let the match slip from the palm of their hands. But, Cameron Green has certainly brought them back into the match with that very late scalp. They haven't bowled poorly and have been a bit unlucky but the English openers, for once showed great positive intent to keep the Aussie pacers at bay. The hosts still have more than 200 runs to play with and if they repeat what the English quicks did in the last session on Day 2, then they can break the English hearts yet again. It is all about which team wants it more. Do the visitors have it in them to fight till the end and see the match through? Or will the Aussies get their mojo back and be all over the visitors in the final session? We'll find out soon. Stay tuned for an exhilarating session coming up at 2:30 pm IST (9 am GMT).

Well then, no one expected this but it has happened. Finally, a session which truly belonged to the visitors, well at least till the last delivery but still, they have given themselves the best possible opportunity to win this Test match. The English pacers cleaned up the Australian tail after the Dinner break and for a change, their openers have looked really good out in the middle. Well, they did until Rory Burns fell at the stroke of Tea and that has slightly altered this match. Still, a long way to go as they require 203 more runs and when one wicket falls down, a team can get lose further wickets in quick succession. The job for the English batters is to get through the final session without losing more than a couple of wickets, max. They can then have a bat in the sunshine tomorrow afternoon and push for victory.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, dear. Oh, dear dear. What has happened there? A session that was dominated by England ends with their opening stand broken! Length ball, just outside off. This comes in with the angle and gets quite close to the off pole. Now, Burns decides to leave it a bit too late and that proves to be his undoing. The ball takes the bottom part of the bat and goes onto hit the stumps! A much-needed wicket for Australia and that is Tea on Day 3!
Commentary.Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Nice and full, on off. Zak Crawley comes forward to block it.
Length, around off. Tapped towards gully.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Nicely done! Length, on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it nicely to the square leg fence.
On a length, but wide enough for Zak to leave it with ease.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a good length, around off. This is driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Full, outside off and Burns leans in to punch it towards covers.

A delayed reaction from Alex Carey behind the stumps but Pat Cummins does go for the review. There is a huge noise and the hosts have to go for the review, hoping to break this opening stand. This might be a huge review in the context of the match. There is nothing on Hotspot and on the UltraEdge there is a tiny little spike but that looks to be after the ball went past the bat. The third umpire looks at it from the front again and decides that there's nothing conclusive. The original decision stands.

NOT OUT! What was that noise then? There was a noise for sure but there doesn't seem to any bat on it! Length ball, around off. Burns looks to block but the ball goes past the bat and goes to the keeper. Warner goes up and so does Green. Carey puts in delayed appeal too but the umpire is unmoved. Cummins moves forward and decides to review this one. Now, the replays roll in. First is Hotspot and there is nothing on it. Now, the UltragEdge is a bit interesting. There is a spike but the front-on angle is cropped and the umpire cannot see if there is a deflection to correlate with the UltraEdge spike. The TV umpire goes back to the front-on vision and that shows no clear deflection. He decides that there is no conclusive evidence and the onfield decision stays.
Length, on off. Blocked out.

FOUR! Great effort by Marnus Labuschagne but it is a boundary! Length ball, outside off. Burns drives it nicely through covers. Marnus Labuschagne chases it and does so till the end. He puts in a slide to bring it back in. The TV umpire is called in to check though. Replays show that his hand just brushed the boundary padding while he tries to pull it back in. Boundary.
Fuller, around off. Burns pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Cameron Green comes on to bowl for the first time in this innings.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Beaten! Boland drags his length back a bit as Zak Crawley is batting out of the crease. He also pushes it wider, outside off. Crawley is beaten as he looks to block it away.
Nice and full, on off. Zak blocks it out.
FOUR! Too fine and helped on its way! Full and down the leg side. Zak Crawley just helps it on its way to the fine leg fence.
On a length, on middle. Worked to short fine leg.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, on middle. Flicked past square leg for one.
Ouch! Short of a length, on off. Zak looks to pull but gets hit on the body.
Well, the win predictor used by the broadcasters is showing a 51-49 chance of winning and it's just in favor of the visitors. Probably a first in this series.
Full, on middle. Burns works it through mid on and they get back for the third. Good shot.
Snorter! This lands just a touch fuller, just outside off and angling away. Burns looks to block from the crease but is beaten.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Tap and run. Length, around off. Zak taps it with soft hands to cover and sets off for a single.
Nicely pushed to mid off by Burns to end the over.
Back of a length, just outside off. Burns gets behind the ball to block it.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Zak gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls to the leg side. A leg bye is taken by the batters.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.

Right on the buzzer, Pat Cummins does go for the review for an LBW decision. Well, it looks to be going well over the stumps and down the leg side as well. UltraEdge confirms that there's no bat on it but Ball Tracker shows that it is very close. In fact, the ball was clipping the top of leg stump but the onfield decision will stay. Australia though don't lose the review which might come in handy later on.

NOT OUT! Full ball, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley shuffles a bit and looks to flick it. The ball hits the pads and there is a big appeal for LBW! The umpire is unmoved again. Cummins runs in towards the pitch and has a word with his players. One of the players says that height should not be an issue and Cummins takes the review with a second left on the clock. The replays roll in. No bat on that and Ball Tracker has the ball clipping the leg stump with umpire's call! A lucky break for England. Had that been given out on field, the review would not have saved Zak Crawley!
On middle, hit on the up towards mid on.
A well-directed shortish ball, over middle and just angling across the left-hander. Burns just about sways away from the line of the ball.
Slightly fuller, on off. Burns presents the full face of the bat and punches it towards mid off.
Short of a good length, angling across off stump. Burns hops back and keeps it out on the off side.

FIFTY-RUN STAND! Back of a length, angling into middle and leg. Crawley works it off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a single. A 50-run opening stand for England! This sight has been rare for them to witness in the recent past, but the English fans have something to cheer about now!
A length ball, around off. Crawley taps it towards the point region.
On a length, on the pads. Zak gets rapped on the pads. The ball rolls past square leg and a single is taken.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out to cover.
Boland bowls it fuller and wider this time. Zak leaves it for Carey.
On a length, outside off. Blocked out.
Full, on off. Burns works it past square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.

FOUR! Cummins strays on the pads and Zak Crawley punishes it! Full, on middle and leg. A step forward and Crawley flicks it past the diving mid on fielder for a boundary. Highest opening pair for England in the series. These two ave looked really good in the middle.
Jaffa! Back of a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley is forced to poke at it but it zips past the outside edge.
Two more now! On a length, around off. Zak gets the inside edge wide of deep backward square leg for a couple. Good running there.
FOUR! Oh, that is lovely! Length ball, around off. Zak Crawley takes a step down the track and nicely works it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Beaten! Angled into middle from wide of the crease, on a length. It goes away a bit after pitching to beat Crawley's attempted defence.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Pat Cummins (3-0-10-0) comes from the opposite end now.

A big appeal for LBW! Full ball, around off. Burns stays in the crease to block it out but gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. The fielders move forward to have a chat. Height is something that is being discussed and they reckon that it might be going over. Not reviewed.
Boland comes 'round the wickets and bowls it full, just outside off. Burns covers the stumps an leaves it.
On a length, right on the off pole. Burns stays back and defends it.
Nice and full, on off. Burns blocks it back to the bowler.
Length, on the body. Worked past square leg for one.
Boland is right on the money! Length ball, landing outside off and coming back in. Zak leaves it with ease though.
Scott Boland comes into the attack now and the crowd gets right behind him.

FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side yet again and Starc just isn't getting his line right here. Burns shuffles a bit and looks to flick it fine. The ball comes off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Full, sliding on the pads. Burns keeps his balance and clips it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. This is a much better start from the English opening pair.

As close as it can get to not hitting the stumps. Good-length ball, around off. Burns looks to block it out but ends up chopping it back onto the stumps. The ball though goes a couple of inches over the middle stump and Burns is maybe due for a little bit of luck in this series.

Not reviewed! It looked to be missing the bat by a fair way but there was a noise for sure. Starc pitches it up, around off and around 145 kph. The ball just moves away off the pitch and zips past Burns' outside edge. Cummins is the voice of reason from mid on and decides not to review it. The replay shows that it didn't hit anything.
Good running. On a length, around off. Crawley is pushed back and he just bunts it out towards covers for a quick single.
Good-looking shot from Rory Burns. A touch fuller, on off. Burns hangs back and punches it through the cover region. Marnus Labuschagne hunts it down and saves a run for his team.
Good-length ball, angled at the body. Crawley looks to work it away leg side but misses. The ball comes off the pads and lands in front of short leg.
Slightly fuller, on off and this is pushed towards mid on.
Back of a length, around middle and tapped towards mid-wicket.
Nicely bowled! A length ball, angled into off and just nibbling away off the pitch. Crawley gets beaten past the outside edge as the ball keeps a bit low as well.
FOUR! Lovely timing from Zak Crawley. Full and angling into middle and leg. Crawley plays an exquisite on drive and picks up a boundary down to the long on fence.

Burns seems to have made an adjustment to his trigger movement as noted by one of the commentators on air. His front foot isn't moving as far across as it was before so he is not really losing his balance. The fourth ball of the previous over was the same delivery that he got in the first Test in Brisbane but this time, he didn't get too far across and neither did Starc get the ball to swing.
Sharp work! Cummins hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Crawley taps it straight to Travis Head at short leg, who keeps Crawley on his toes.
On a length, around off and left alone.
Short of a length, well outside off. Rory Burns' eyes lit up as he looks to thrash it away but just that hint of away movement and he gets beaten past the outside edge.
FOUR! Nicely put away. Starc goes full and at the pads. Burns flicks it through the vacant mid-wicket region and picks up a boundary.
Good-length, angled into middle and leg. Burns gets caught on the crease and gets pinged on the thigh pad.

Anxious moment out there in the middle and the last thing the visitors need is another run out. Back of a length, Burns is on the back foot and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Crawley looks for the single but Burns doesn't even know where the ball is. Crawley retreats in time.
Pitched up, on middle. Burns blocks it out.
Ooh, that one did swing in a mile. Cummins bowls this one from wider of the crease and the ball swings in late as Crawley makes the leave.
On off. Defended off the front foot.

That would have to be swinging in a mile to get the LBW decision. An in-dipper this time from Cummins. This one pitches well outside off and Crawley just strides out but offers no shot. The ball hits the pads but the umpire isn't interested.

FOUR! Edged and just past third slip! A lovely delivery angled into middle and straightening away after pitching. Crawley gets squared up and the outside edge is found. The ball flies past Usman Khawaja's dive at third slip and races away into the fence.
Around the fifth-stump line and an easy leave for Crawley.
Slightly fuller, around off. Crawley in two minds and decides to leave it at the last second. The ball comes off the toe end of the bat and drops dead near Crawley.
Well bowled. Starc surprises Burns with a really full delivery, on middle and shaping away. Burns does well to get a bat on it.
This is angled at the pads and swinging away. Burns looks to play it square but again looks to be falling over and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but not a big appeal.
Zak Crawley is off the mark. Over middle, Crawley wrists it towards fine leg for a single. A big cheer from the crowd as Boland collects the ball. Familiar scenes now.
A touch fuller and wider, at 149 kph. Crawley isn't interested in playing at that one.
Around the off stump and looking to bring it back in. Crawley shoulders arms.
Maybe just nipping back in a bit too much. A length ball, on middle and shaping back in. Crawley looks to punch it back but gets an inside edge onto the pads and that's what saved him.
Pitched up, in that channel around the off stump. This one holds its line but Burns makes an assured leave yet again.
Length again, just a little bit wider. Burns edges it down through backward point with soft hands and picks up a couple.
Around the top of off and Burns hangs back to defend.
A touch shorter in length, around leg. Burns gets cramped for room and hit on the thigh pad.
Cummins goes fuller and pushes it across the off stump. The ball is around 133 kph but this one just zips through and has good carry on it as well.
A good-length ball, angled across the off stump. Burns makes an assured leave.
Cummins is set to steam in.

FOUR LEG BYES! Just hasn't got his rhythm right yet, Mitchell Starc. On the pads again and Zak Crawley goes for the flick. The ball goes off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence. So, 9 off the first over. A positive start for the visitors.
Starc looks to attack the pads and puts a bit extra behind this one as he bowls it around 147 kph. He spills it well down the leg side though.
Fuller one, at 144 kph and on off. Burns stands tall and drives it past extra cover for a single.
Good-length ball, angled into the body. Burns looks to tuck it away leg side but the ball just zips through and catches Burns in the mid riff.

FOUR! Edgy boundary but Rory Burns is up and running. Starc angles this one in at off stump and the ball straightens after pitching. Burns gets squared up but luckily for him, the outside edge drops short and goes between third slip and gully for a boundary. He is off the pair. The change of hair has worked!
Starc steams in first ball but spills it down the leg side. Burns looks for the flick but misses.
